INSERT INTO `word` VALUES ('6畳','6张榻榻米垫','6-Jō','\n','2019-11-27',1,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=6畳&tl=ja&tk=189021.316969&client=webapp&prev=input'),('Ability','（体力或智力方面的）能力；才能，才智（用于把以 -able 或 -ible 结尾的形容词转化为名词，表示这些形容词具有的特性）…性','uk :əˈbɪl.ə.ti, us :əˈbɪl.ə.t̬i','[There s no doubting her ability. \n 她的能力毋庸置疑。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n She had the ability to explain things clearly and concisely. \n 她有能力简单扼要地把事情解释清楚。 \n, She s a woman of considerable abilities. \n 她是个非常有才干的女性。 \n, I have children in my class of very mixed abilities (= different levels of skill or intelligence). \n 我班里孩子们的能力参差不齐。 \n, a mixed-ability class \n 不同能力水平的学生混编的班级 \n, suitability \n 适宜性 \n, vulnerability \n 脆弱性 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukabd/ukabdic018.mp3'),('Abundant','大量的；充足的；丰富的','uk :əˈbʌn.dənt, us :əˈbʌn.dənt','[an abundant supply of food \n 充足的食品供应 \n, There is abundant evidence that cars have a harmful effect on the environment. \n 有充分的证据表明，汽车对环境有害。 \n, Cheap consumer goods are abundant (= exist in large amounts) in this part of the world. \n 在这个地区，大量的低廉消费品充斥其间。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukabs/ukabsor019.mp3'),('Accumulate','积累；积聚；积攒逐渐增加；逐渐升高','uk :əˈkjuː.mjə.leɪt, us :əˈkjuː.mjə.leɪt','[As people accumulate more wealth, they tend to spend a greater proportion of their incomes. \n 人们积累了更多财富后，他们的花费占收入的比重也往往会增加。 \n, The company said the debt was accumulated during its acquisition of nine individual businesses. \n 该公司称其在收购9家个体公司的过程中，债务越积越多。 \n, We ve accumulated so much rubbish over the years. \n 多年来我们已经堆积了这么多的垃圾。 \n, A thick layer of dust had accumulated in the room. \n 房间里积了厚厚一层灰尘。 \n, If you don t go through the papers on your desk on a regular basis, they just keep on accumulating. \n 如果你不去定期整理办公桌上的文件，它们就会越积越多。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukacc/ukaccou011.mp3'),('Accurate','准确的；精确的；正确的','uk :ˈæk.jə.rət, us :ˈæk.jɚ.ət','[an accurate machine \n 精密的机器 \n, an accurate description \n 准确的描述 \n, The figures they have used are just not accurate. \n 他们引用的数字太不准确。 \n, Her novel is an accurate reflection of life in Spain. \n 她的小说是西班牙生活的真实写照。 \n, We hope to become more accurate in predicting earthquakes. \n 我们希望能更准确地预报地震。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukacc/ukaccou015.mp3'),('Accustomed','习惯的；适应了的一贯的；惯常的','uk :əˈkʌs.təmd, us :əˈkʌs.təmd','[She quickly became accustomed to his messy ways. \n 她很快就习惯了他的邋遢作风。 \n, I m not accustomed to being treated like this. \n 我不习惯别人这样待我。 \n, She performed the task with her accustomed ease. \n 她以一贯的轻松自如完成了任务。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukacc/ukaccou026.mp3'),('Acquire','取得，获得；购得；学到','uk :əˈkwaɪər, us :əˈkwaɪɚ','[He acquired the firm in 2008. \n 他于2008年收购了这家公司。 \n, I was wearing a newly/recently acquired jacket. \n 我穿着一件新买的夹克衫。 \n, I seem to have acquired (= have got although I don t know how) two copies of this book. \n 这本书我好像买重了。 \n, He has acquired a reputation for being difficult to work with. \n 据说很难跟他共事。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukacq/ukacqua008.mp3'),('Adamant','固执的；坚决的，坚定不移的','uk :ˈæd.ə.mənt, us :ˈæd.ə.mənt','[[ + that ] \n I ve told her she should stay at home and rest but she s adamant that she s coming. \n 我告诉过她应该在家休息，可她坚持要来。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukact/ukactiv027.mp3'),('Adequate','足够的；合格的；合乎需要的','uk :ˈæd.ə.kwət, us :ˈæd.ə.kwət','[Have we got adequate food for 20 guests? \n 我们的食物够招待20位客人吗？ \n, I didn t have adequate time to prepare. \n 我没有充足的时间来准备。 \n, It s not a big salary but it s adequate for our needs. \n 工资虽不优厚，但足以满足我们的需要了。 \n, The council s provision for the elderly is barely adequate (= is not enough). \n 市政会给老年人提供的保障不足。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Will future oil supplies be adequate to meet world needs? \n 未来的石油供应能满足世界的需要吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukada/ukadapt029.mp3'),('Adjacent','邻近的；毗连的','uk :əˈdʒeɪ.sənt, us :əˈdʒeɪ.sənt','[They work in adjacent buildings. \n 他们在相邻的两座楼里工作。 \n, They lived in a house adjacent to the railway. \n 他们家住在铁路旁边。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukadh/ukadher014.mp3'),('Adorable','可爱的；讨人喜欢的','uk :əˈdɔː.rə.bəl, us :əˈdɔːr.ə.bəl','[She has the most adorable two-year-old girl. \n 她两岁的小女儿真是可爱极了。 \n, an adorable puppy \n 可爱的小狗 \n]\n','2019-11-19',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukadm/ukadmon012.mp3'),('Adverse','不利的；负面的；有害的','uk :ˈæd.vɜːs, us :ædˈvɝːs','[The match has been cancelled because of adverse weather conditions. \n 由于天气恶劣，这场比赛已被取消。 \n, They received a lot of adverse publicity/criticism about the changes. \n 这些变化为他们招致种种负面报道／非难。 \n, So far the drug is thought not to have any adverse effects. \n 迄今为止，人们一直认为这种药物没有任何副作用。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukadu/ukadult025.mp3'),('Aggregate','聚集体，集成体；总数，合计骨料，集料，粒料（建筑用的小石料）合计的，总的；总数的使聚集，使积聚','uk :ˈæɡ.rɪ.ɡət, us :ˈæɡ.rə.ɡət','[They purchased an aggregate of 3,000 shares in the company. \n 他们总共买了这家公司的3000股股票。 \n, Snowflakes are loose aggregates of ice crystals. \n 雪花是冰晶松散的凝聚体。 \n, Arsenal lost the second game, but got through to the final on aggregate (= adding together the goals in both matches). \n 阿森纳队虽然输了第二场比赛，但是凭借进球总数进入了决赛。 \n, Volumes of aggregates, cement, and concrete used in the UK will rise this year. \n 今年英国骨料、水泥和混凝土的使用量都将上升。 \n, The seven companies have an aggregate turnover of £5.2 million. \n 这7家公司的总营业额为520万英镑。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukage/ukage__019.mp3'),('Agriculturally','农业科学','ˌæɡrɪˈkʌltʃ(ə)rəl','null\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'null'),('Alternative','（计划或方法）可替代的；可供选择的非传统的；另类的（尤指不同于平常事物的）可供选择的事物；可供选择的解决办法','uk :ɒlˈtɜː.nə.tɪv, us :ɑːlˈtɝː.nə.t̬ɪv','[The opposition parties have so far failed to set out an alternative strategy. \n 反对党到目前为止还没有提出其他的策略。 \n, An alternative venue for the concert is being sought. \n 正在寻找其他可举办音乐会的地方。 \n, alternative comedy \n 另类喜剧 \n, an alternative to coffee \n 咖啡代用品 \n, There must be an alternative to people sleeping on the streets. \n 一定要想法解决街头露宿者的问题。 \n, I m afraid I have no alternative but to ask you to leave (= that is what I have to do). \n 恐怕我别无选择，只有让你离开。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukalt/ukaltar009.mp3'),('Amateur','业余爱好的，非职业的业余的；（尤指）业余体育运动的业余爱好者；业余运动员外行；粗通（某一行）的人','uk :ˈæm.ə.tər, us :ˈæm.ə.tʃɚ','[an amateur astronomer/boxer/historian \n 业余天文学爱好者／拳击手／历史学爱好者 \n, He was an amateur singer until the age of 40, when he turned professional. \n 40岁之前他一直是个业余歌手，之后才转为职业歌手。 \n, amateur athletics \n 业余运动员 \n, This tennis tournament is open to both amateurs and professionals. \n 这次网球锦标赛业余运动员和职业运动员都可以参加。 \n, I won t be giving them any more work - they re a bunch of amateurs. \n 我有活也再不给他们干了，简直就是一帮外行。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukama/ukamalg007.mp3'),('Ambiguous','含糊不清的；引起歧义的，模棱两可的；不明确的','uk :æmˈbɪɡ.ju.əs, us :æmˈbɪɡ.ju.əs','[His reply to my question was somewhat ambiguous. \n 他对我的提问回答得有些含糊不清。 \n, The wording of the agreement is ambiguous. \n 该协议的措词模棱两可。 \n, The government has been ambiguous on this issue. \n 在此问题上政府立场一直不明确。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukama/ukamalg026.mp3'),('Ambitious','有抱负的；志向远大的；雄心勃勃的（计划、想法）要求过高的；需要极大努力及才干的；费劲的','uk :æmˈbɪʃ.əs, us :æmˈbɪʃ.əs','[an ambitious young lawyer \n 雄心勃勃的年轻律师 \n, He s very ambitious for his children (= he wants them to be successful). \n 他望子成龙。 \n, She has some ambitious plans for her business. \n 她雄心勃勃，打算扩大经营规模。 \n, The government has announced an ambitious plan to modernize the railway network. \n 政府已经宣布了实现铁路网现代化的宏伟规划。 \n, The original completion date was over-ambitious, so we have had to delay the opening. \n 当初在确定完工日期的时候太雄心勃勃，后来我们不得不把落成典礼推迟。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukama/ukamalg030.mp3'),('Amend','修订，修正，修改（法律文件等）','uk :əˈmend, us :əˈmend','[MPs were urged to amend the law to prevent another oil tanker disaster. \n 下院议员们被敦促修订该法律，以防止油轮泄漏灾难再次发生。 \n, In line 20,  men  should be amended (= changed) to  people . \n 第20行中的 men 应改为 people。 \n, Until the constitution is amended, the power to appoint ministers will remain with the president. \n 在宪法修正之前，总统仍然有权任命部长。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukamb/ukambit018.mp3'),('Ample','足够的，充足的，充裕的（身躯）肥大的，粗壮的，丰满的','uk :ˈæm.pəl, us :ˈæm.pəl','[You ll have ample opportunity to ask questions after the talk. \n 演讲结束后你们会有足够的时间提问。 \n, There s ample evidence that the lawyer knew exactly what she was doing. \n 有充分的证据表明，该律师十分清楚她自己在做什么。 \n, They had ample warning of the factory closure. \n 对于工厂的倒闭，他们早就得到了大量警告。 \n, her ample bosom \n 她丰满的胸部 \n, His ample girth (= his big stomach) was clear evidence of his passion for food. \n 从他那大腹便便的样子一眼就能看出，他是个非常好吃的人。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukamo/ukamort017.mp3'),('Annual','一年一度的；每年的一年的年刊，年报；（尤指）儿童年册（学校或其他机构出版的）年刊，年鉴一年生植物','uk :ˈæn.ju.əl, us :ˈæn.ju.əl','[an annual event/visit/holiday \n 年度大事／每年一次的访问／每年的假期 \n, Companies publish annual reports to inform the public about the previous year s activities. \n 公司发布年度报告，告知公众上一年的具体业务。 \n, annual income/salary/profit \n 年收入／年薪／年利润 \n]\n','2019-12-20',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukann/ukannou007.mp3'),('Anomaly','异常的人（或事物）；不规则；（同一种类中的）畸形','uk :əˈnɒm.ə.li, us :əˈnɑː.mə.li','[Statistical anomalies can make it difficult to compare economic data from one year to the next. \n 统计上的不规范会使年与年之间的经济数据难以互相比较。 \n, The anomaly of the social security system is that you sometimes have more money without a job. \n 社会保障制度下的反常现象是，失业有时反而拿钱更多。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukann/ukannou023.mp3'),('Antagonize','使对抗，使对立；引起…的敌意（或反感）','uk :ænˈtæɡ.ə.naɪz, us :ænˈtæɡ.ə.naɪz','[It s a very delicate situation and I ve no wish to antagonize him. \n 这是一种很棘手的局面，而我无意使他和我反目成仇。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukano/ukanore014.mp3'),('Antonym','反义词','uk :ˈæn.tə.nɪm, us :ˈæn.t̬ən.ɪm',NULL,'2019-10-03',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukant/ukantis007.mp3'),('Arbitrary','任意的；随机的；随心所欲的专断的；武断的；霸道的','uk :ˈɑː.bɪ.trər.i, us :ˈɑːr.bə.trer.i','[arbitrary decision-making \n 随意决策 \n, Did you have a reason for choosing your destination or was it arbitrary? \n 你根据什么选择目的地？还是随意选定的？ \n, an arbitrary ruler \n 专制的统治者 \n, The company has been the subject of an arbitrary take-over. \n 这家公司被强行接管。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaqu/ukaquat018.mp3'),('Arduous','艰难的，艰巨的；费力的','uk :ˈɑː.dʒu.əs, us :ˈɑːr.dʒu.əs','[an arduous climb/task/journey \n 举步维艰的攀登／艰巨的任务／艰难的旅程 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukarc/ukarchi011.mp3'),('Arrogant','傲慢的；狂妄自大的；趾高气扬的','uk :ˈær.ə.ɡənt, us :ˈer-','[I found him arrogant and rude. \n 我觉得他这个人狂妄自大、粗鲁无礼。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukarr/ukarriv005.mp3'),('Assuage','缓和；减轻；平息','uk :əˈsweɪdʒ, us :əˈsweɪdʒ','[The government has tried to assuage the public s fears. \n 政府努力消除公众的恐慌。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukass/ukassiz011.mp3'),('Assume','假定，假设；臆断，想当然地认为冒充，冒称；假装，装出承担，担任；僭取，夺取；呈现，具有','uk :əˈsjuːm, us :əˈsuːm','[[ + (that) ] \n I assumed (that) you knew each other because you went to the same school. \n 你们不是上的同一所学校嘛？我还以为你们两个认识呢。 \n, Let s assume (that) they re coming and make plans on that basis. \n 我们还是假定他们会来，并以此来作出计划。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We can t assume the suspects to be guilty simply because they ve decided to remain silent. \n 我们不能仅仅因为疑犯选择保持沉默就断定他们有罪。 \n, We mustn t assume the suspects  guilt. \n 我们千万不能臆断犯罪嫌疑人有罪。 \n, Moving to a different town, he assumed a false name. \n 搬家到了另外一个城镇后，他用了个假名字。 \n, During the investigation, two detectives assumed the identities of antiques dealers. \n 在案件调查中，两名侦探假装成古董商。 \n, He assumed a look of indifference but I knew how he felt. \n 他装出一副无所谓的样子，但我明白他的内心感受。 \n, The new president assumes office at midnight tonight. \n 新总统在今晚午夜就职。 \n, The terrorists assumed control of the plane and forced it to land in the desert. \n 恐怖分子控制了飞机，并使其迫降在沙漠中。 \n, The issue has assumed considerable political proportions (= has become a big political problem). \n 这已经成为一个很大的政治问题。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukass/ukassiz012.mp3'),('Attitude','心态；看法；态度自信姿态，姿势','uk :ˈæt.ɪ.tʃuːd, us :ˈæt̬.ə.tuːd','[It s often very difficult to change people s attitudes. \n 人们对事情的看法通常很难改变。 \n, [ + that ] \n She takes the attitude that children should be allowed to learn at their own pace. \n 在儿童学习步调快慢的问题上，她的态度是应顺其自然。 \n, He has a very bad attitude to/towards work. \n 他的工作态度极差。 \n, He seems to have undergone a change in/of attitude recently, and has become much more cooperative. \n 他的态度近来好像转变了，变得合作多了。 \n, I don t like your attitude (= the way you are behaving). \n 我不喜欢你这种态度。 \n, That boy has a real attitude problem (= behaves in a way that makes it difficult for other people to have a relationship with him or work with him). \n 那个孩子的态度很成问题。 \n, She lay sprawled across the sofa, in an attitude of complete abandon. \n 她四肢摊开躺在沙发上，一副完全无拘无束的样子。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukatt/ukatten009.mp3'),('Augment','提高；增大；加强','uk :ɔːɡˈment, us :ɑːɡˈment','[He would have to find work to augment his income. \n 他可能不得不找活儿干来增加收入。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaud/ukaudac018.mp3'),('Berate','严责，训斥','uk :bɪˈreɪt, us :bɪˈreɪt','[As he left the meeting, he was berated by angry demonstrators. \n 他离开会场时遭到了愤怒的示威者责骂。 \n, Doctors are often berated for being poor communicators, particularly when they have to give patients bad news. \n 医生常常因不善于沟通遭受指责，特别是当他们必须告诉病人坏消息的时候。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukben/ukbenev017.mp3'),('Boost','改善；提高；增强；推动改善；提高；增强；推动','uk :buːst, us :buːst','[The theatre managed to boost its audiences by cutting ticket prices. \n 剧院设法通过降低票价来增加观众数量。 \n, Share prices were boosted by reports of the president s recovery. \n 总统康复的报道推动股票价格上扬。 \n, I tried to boost his ego (= make him feel more confident) by praising his cooking. \n 我赞扬他的厨艺，试图以此增强他的自信心。 \n, The lowering of interest rates will give a much-needed boost to the economy. \n 利率的下调将会给经济注入急需的推动力。 \n, Passing my driving test was such a boost to my confidence. \n 通过了驾照考试使我自信心大增。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboo/ukboomi007.mp3'),('Bouncer','（酒吧、聚会等雇用的）保安，保镖','uk :ˈbaʊn.sər, us :ˈbaʊn.sɚ','[]\n','2019-10-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbot/ukbothe022.mp3'),('Bristle','短而硬的毛；刚毛刷子毛（毛发等）直立生气','uk :ˈbrɪs.əl, us :ˈbrɪs.əl','[The old woman had a few grey bristles sprouting from her chin. \n 老妇人下巴上长出几根灰白的又短又硬的毛。 \n, The best quality men s shaving brushes are made from badger bristle. \n 最好的男用修面刷由獾毛制成。 \n, My toothbrush has blue and white plastic bristles. \n 我的牙刷上有蓝白塑料刷毛。 \n, The cat s fur bristled and it arched its back. \n 那只猫竖起了毛，弓起了背。 \n, She bristled at the suggestion that she had in any way neglected the child. \n 人们认为她多少有点忽略了这孩子，这种看法使她很生气。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbri/ukbriga029.mp3'),('Catacomb','（旧时由纵横通道和若干房室构成的）地下墓穴','uk :ˈkæt.ə.kuːm, us :ˈkæt̬.ə.kuːm','[They went down into catacombs beneath the church. \n 他们进入了教堂的地下墓穴。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcas/ukcaste014.mp3'),('Conservative','保守的；守旧的（外表上）保守的，传统的，不赶潮流的（猜测、计算）保守的，低估的（英国）保守党的保守，守旧；保守主义','uk :kənˈsɜː.və.tɪv, us :kənˈsɝː.və.t̬ɪv','[a conservative society/outlook \n 保守的社会／观念 \n, Older people tend to be more conservative and a bit suspicious of anything new. \n 上年纪的人往往很保守，对任何新的东西都有些怀疑。 \n, He\'s a very conservative dresser - he always looks like he\'s wearing his father\'s clothes! \n 他穿着十分保守——看上去总像是穿着他父亲的衣服！ \n, If I said there were three million unemployed, that would be a conservative estimate. \n 我要是说失业人数有300万的话，那是保守估计。 \n, the Conservative Party \n 保守党 \n, Conservative policies \n 保守党奉行的政策 \n, a Conservative MP/government \n 保守党议员／政府 \n, Did you vote Conservative at the last election? \n 上次选举你投的是保守党的票吗？ \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc026.mp3'),('Eclipse','日食；月食黯然失色遮掩（天体的）光掩没…的重要性（或优点、声誉等）；凌驾…之上；光芒盖过…','uk :ɪˈklɪps, us :ɪˈklɪps','[a solar/lunar eclipse \n 日／月食 \n, On Wednesday there will be a total/partial eclipse of the sun. \n 周三将有一次日全／偏食。 \n, The eclipse of the ruling political party was inevitable. \n 执政党大势已去，无可挽回。 \n, His remarkable contribution to literature has been too long in eclipse. \n 他对文学的杰出贡献已被人们遗忘太久了。 \n, The moon will be totally eclipsed at 12.10 p.m.  \n 晚上12点10分会出现月全食。 \n, The economy has eclipsed all other issues during this election campaign. \n 这次大选期间，经济问题成为压倒一切的重大议题。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukec_/ukec___023.mp3'),('Hyena','鬣狗','uk :haɪˈiː.nə, us :haɪˈiː.nə','[]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhur/ukhurly026.mp3'),('Imprisonment','非法拘禁，非法拘留','uk :ˌfɒls ɪmˈprɪz.ən.mənt, us :ˌfɑːls ɪmˈprɪz.ən.mənt','[He brought civil proceedings against the police for false imprisonment. \n 他向法庭提起民事诉讼，控告警方非法拘留。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/uka32/uka32793.mp3'),('Inch','英寸（约合2.54厘米，有时用符号\'表示）缓慢地移动','uk :ɪntʃ, us :ɪntʃ','[Twelve inches are equal to one foot. \n 12英寸等于1英尺。 \n, He had a cut an inch long above his left eye. \n 他左眼上方有一道1英寸长的伤口。 \n, The snow was six inches deep in some places. \n 有些地方积雪有6英寸深。 \n, a piece of wood 2″ by 2″ \n 一块两英寸见方的木块 \n, We are inching towards an agreement. \n 我们在慢慢努力达成共识。 \n, Share prices inched up/higher during the day. \n 今日股价缓慢攀升。 \n, Residents watched the flames inch closer and closer. \n 居民们望着火舌一步步逼近。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinc/ukincen010.mp3'),('Isle','（尤用于地名）岛','uk :aɪl, us :aɪl','[Explore the more remote Caribbean isles. \n 探索更加遥远的加勒比岛。 \n, the Isle of Skye \n 斯凯岛 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukair/ukairwo004.mp3'),('Murphy','墨菲法则（一种认为凡有可能出差错的事终将出差错的论断）','uk :ˌmɜː.fiz ˈlɔː, us :ˌmɝː.fiz ˈlɑː','[The bus is always late but today when I was late it came on time - that s Murphy s law! \n 那一路公共汽车总是晚点，可是今天我迟到了，它却准时来了——我想那一定是墨菲法则在起作用。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmun/ukmunif012.mp3'),('Murphy bed','墨菲床','Mò fēi chuáng','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=Murphy bed&tl=ja&tk=182362.326702&client=webapp&prev=input'),('Nacre','珠母层，珍珠母','uk :ˈneɪ.kər, us :-kɚ','[]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd19/epd19858.mp3'),('Neutral','中立的，不偏不倚的（体育比赛）中立场地不引人注意的（化学物质）中性的，既非酸性又非碱性的（物理学中）中性的，不带电的空档不活动；停滞中立者','uk :ˈnjuː.trəl, us :ˈnuː.trəl','[If there s an argument between my daughter and her mother, it s important that I remain neutral. \n 如果我女儿和她母亲发生争吵，我保持中立是很重要的。 \n, The peace conference would have to be held in a neutral country. \n 和平会议必须在一个中立国举行。 \n, I d rather meet on neutral ground/territory (= somewhere not controlled by or connected to either of us) rather than in his apartment. \n 我宁愿在一个与双方都无关的地方和他见面，而不是在他的公寓里。 \n, K \n The final will, of course, be played at a neutral ground.  \n 决赛当然会在中立场地举行。 \n, S \n The Superbowl always takes place on a neutral field. \n 超级碗比赛总是在中立场地举行。 \n, Kelly wants dark red walls, but I d like a more neutral colour like cream. \n 凯莉想把墙弄成暗红色，而我更喜欢乳白之类的中性色。 \n, Pure water is neutral and has a pH of 7. \n 纯水是中性的，pH值为7。 \n, Atoms consist of positively-charged protons, negatively-charged electrons and neutral particles called neutrons. \n 原子由带正电的质子、带负电的电子和称为中子的不带电粒子组成。 \n, to leave the car in neutral \n 把车挂空挡 \n, After two years in neutral, the economy is finally moving forward again. \n 经济停滞了两年后终于再次向前发展。 \n, Sweden and Switzerland were neutrals during the war. \n 在战争期间，瑞典和瑞士是中立国。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneu/ukneuro011.mp3'),('Nine-times-outta-ten','九倍十','Jiǔ bèi shí','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=Nine-times-outta-ten&tl=ja&tk=426930.47046&client=webapp&prev=input'),('Obliterate','彻底毁掉，抹去，覆盖（使不留痕迹）忘却，抹掉（想法或感情）','uk :əˈblɪt.ər.eɪt, us :əˈblɪt̬.ə.reɪt','[The missile strike was devastating - the target was totally obliterated. \n 这次导弹袭击是毁灭性的——目标荡然无存。 \n, All of a sudden the view was obliterated by the fog. \n 突然之间雾气淹没了这片景象。 \n, Maybe she gets drunk to obliterate painful memories. \n 也许她喝醉酒是为了忘却痛苦的往事。 \n]\n','2019-11-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobj/ukobjec018.mp3'),('Pearl','珍珠珍珠首饰人造珍珠液态珠状物珠灰色，银白色珍珠母（同 mother-of-pearl）','uk :pɜːl, us :pɝːl','[a string of pearls \n 一串珍珠 \n, a pearl necklace \n 珍珠项链 \n, He gave her pearls for her birthday. \n 他送给她珍珠首饰作为生日礼物。 \n, cultured pearls \n 养殖的珍珠 \n, There were pearls of dew on the grass. \n 草地上有点点露珠。 \n, pearl buttons \n 珍珠母纽扣 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpay/ukpayro030.mp3'),('Peppermint','（尤指用来给糖果提味的）（胡椒）薄荷（胡椒）薄荷糖','uk :ˈpep.ə.mɪnt, us :ˈpep.ɚ.mɪnt','[She drinks peppermint-flavoured tea. \n 她喝薄荷味的茶。 \n, You can eat a peppermint as a breath freshener. \n 你可以吃一块薄荷糖清一下口气。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpente014.mp3'),('Phantom','幽灵；鬼魂像幽灵的；像鬼魂的幻觉的；幻影的；虚假的','uk :ˈfæn.təm, us :ˈfæn.t̬əm','[A phantom coach is said to pass through the grounds of this house when there s a full moon. \n 据说月圆时一辆幽灵马车就会从这座房子的庭院里驶过。 \n, umorous \n The phantom wine-drinker has been around (= an unknown person has been drinking the wine)! \n 附近一定有嗜酒幽灵出没！ \n, Although she had to have her leg amputated, she still feels as though she s got a phantom limb. \n 尽管不得已把一条腿截去了，但她仍觉得自己仿佛有条虚幻的腿。 \n, They discovered it was a phantom organization set up for the processing of drug profits. \n 他们发现这只是一个遮人耳目、处理毒品利润的组织。 \n, K \n Although she grew bigger, she later discovered it was a phantom (US false) pregnancy. \n 尽管她肚子越来越大，但后来却发现是精神性假妊娠。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpff/ukpfft_015.mp3'),('Professing','声称；自称；谎称','uk :prəˈfes, us :prəˈfes','[[ + to infinitive ] \n She professes not to be interested in money. \n 她声称对钱不感兴趣。 \n, I don t profess to know all the details about the case. \n 我不敢妄称了解这个案件的所有细节。 \n, She professes ignorance of the whole affair, though I m not sure I believe her. \n 她声称对整个事件一无所知，但我不能确定是否该相信她。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprod_020.mp3'),('Senate','（美国、澳大利亚、法国等国的）参议院（大学的）评议会，理事会','uk :ˈsen.ət, us :ˈsen.ət','[the French/Australian Senate \n 法国／澳大利亚参议院 \n, The US Senate has 100 members. \n 美国参议院有100名参议员。 \n, The law has no chance of being passed by the Senate. \n 这条法律不可能在参议院得到通过。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksen/uksen__002.mp3'),('Senator','参议员','uk :ˈsen.ə.tər, us :ˈsen.ə.t̬ɚ','[Only two senators voted against the bill. \n 只有两名参议员反对这一法案。 \n, [ as form of address ] \n It\'s a pleasure to meet you, Senator. \n 很高兴认识你，参议员。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksen/uksen__003.mp3'),('Sinocentrism','中国中心主义者','/ˌsɪnəʊˈsɛntɹɪzəm/','null\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'null'),('Sovereign','君主；元首；最高统治者金镑（英国于1817-1914年之间使用的面值为1英镑的金币）至高无上的；完全独立的灵丹妙药','uk :ˈsɒv.ər.ɪn, us :ˈsɑːv.rən','[Sovereign power is said to lie with the people in some countries, and with a ruler in others. \n 据说，在一些国家中最高统治权归于人民，而在另一些国家则掌握在统治者手中。 \n, We must respect the rights of sovereign states/nations to conduct their own affairs. \n 我们必须尊重独立主权国家处理本国事务的权利。 \n, Love is a sovereign remedy for unhappiness. \n 爱是治疗悲伤的灵丹妙药。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksouth009.mp3'),('Spondulix','（幽默的说法）货币；钱，金钱；财产','uk :spɒnˈduː.lɪks, us :sp