inese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukatt/ukatten010.mp3'),('aura','气氛，氛围；气息（一些人声称在人或动物身体周围看到的）光环，光轮','uk :ˈɔː.rə, us :ˈɔːr.ə','[The woods have an aura of mystery. \n 这片树林透着神秘的气息。 \n, There s an aura of sadness about him. \n 他看上去一副悲伤的样子。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaud/ukaudac027.mp3'),('automate','使自动化','uk :ˈɔː.tə.meɪt, us :ˈɑː.t̬ə-','[Massive investment is needed to automate the production process. \n 要实现生产过程的自动化需要大量的投资。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukautis021.mp3'),('autonomy','自治，自治权自主，自主权','uk :ɔːˈtɒn.ə.mi, us :ɑːˈtɑː.nə.mi','[Demonstrators demanded immediate autonomy for their region. \n 游行示威者要求立即实现该地区的自治。 \n, The universities want to preserve their autonomy from central government. \n 大学都希望维护其自主办学权，不受中央政府的控制。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton002.mp3'),('averse','反对的；嫌恶的；不愿意的','uk :əˈvɜːs, us :əˈvɝːs','[Few people are averse to the idea of a free holiday. \n 几乎没有人会反对免费假期这个主意。 \n, I\'m not averse to (= I like) the occasional glass of champagne myself. \n 我乐得偶尔自己来杯香槟酒。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton027.mp3'),('avert','防止，避免转移（目光、想法等）；把…转（向别处）','uk :əˈvɜːt, us :əˈvɝːt',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/ukaut/ukauton029.mp3'),('backstop','（英国圆场棒球运动中的）接手（棒球）接手（catcher的非正式说法）（棒球场上的）挡球网','uk :ˈbæk.stɒp, us :ˈbæk.stɑːp',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbac/ukbackc030.mp3'),('bandit','土匪；盗贼；暴徒','uk :ˈbæn.dɪt, us :ˈbæn.dɪt','[]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbal/ukballs027.mp3'),('barrage','掩护炮火，阻击火网连珠炮一样的（投诉、批评或质问），接二连三的…堰；拦河坝；拦潮坝','uk :ˈbær.ɑːʒ, us :bəˈrɑːʒ','[an artillery barrage \n 炮火掩护 \n, The TV station has received a barrage of complaints about the amount of violence in the series. \n 电视台接到了一连串的投诉，批评电视剧中的暴力镜头太多。 \n, He faced a barrage of questions over his handling of the problem. \n 就该问题的处理方式，他受到了接二连三的质问。 \n, The proposed tidal barrage would generate enough electricity to supply 80,000 homes. \n 提议修筑的拦潮坝发电量将足够8万户家庭使用。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq007.mp3'),('barrel','桶桶（一桶石油相当于159升）枪管飞驰','uk :ˈbær.əl, us :ˈber.əl','[They drank a whole barrel of beer (= the contents of a barrel) at the party. \n 聚会上他们喝了整整一桶啤酒。 \n, We were barrelling along the autobahn at 180 kph. \n 我们以每小时180公里的速度在高速路上飞驰。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbar/ukbaroq009.mp3'),('bastion','堡垒棱堡（城堡和堡垒的突出部分）','uk :ˈbæs.ti.ən, us :ˈbæs.ti.ən','[British public schools are regarded as one of the last bastions of upper-class privilege. \n 英国公学被视为上流阶级特权的最后堡垒之一。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbas/ukbashf029.mp3'),('batter','连续猛打（尤指妇女、儿童）（用面粉、鸡蛋和牛奶调成的）面糊（棒球等的）击球员','uk :ˈbæt.ər, us :ˈbæt̬.ɚ',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbat/ukbatch021.mp3'),('beckon',':ˈbek.ən,','uk','[The customs official beckoned the woman to his counter. \n 海关官员示意那个妇女到他桌前来。 \n, \"Hey you!\" she called, beckoning me over with her finger. \n “嘿，叫你呢！”她喊道，并用手指示意我过去。 \n, He beckoned to me, as if he wanted to speak to me. \n 他给我打手势，好像是要跟我说什么。 \n, For many young people, the bright lights of the city beckon, though a lot of them end up sleeping on the streets. \n 城市璀璨的灯火吸引了许多年轻人，然而其中许多人却最终落得露宿街头。 \n, She\'s an excellent student, for whom a wonderful future beckons. \n 她是个优秀的学生，美妙的前程向她召唤。 \n]','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'null'),('bent','（bent 的过去式及过去分词）弯曲的；不直的；不平的（尤指当权者）不诚实的（尤指男性）同性恋的天赋','uk :bent, us :bent',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukben/ukbenev012.mp3'),('bestow','赠予；给予','uk :bɪˈstəʊ, us :bɪˈstoʊ','[The George Cross is a decoration that is bestowed upon/on British civilians for acts of great bravery. \n 乔治十字勋章是为了表彰英国平民的英勇行为而颁发的。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbes/ukbesid017.mp3'),('bilateral','双边的，双方的','uk :ˌbaɪˈlæt.ər.əl, us :ˌbaɪˈlæt̬.ɚ.əl','[France and Germany have signed a bilateral agreement to help prevent drug smuggling. \n 法国和德国已经签署了一项双边协定以防止毒品走私。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbif/ukbiff_025.mp3'),('boast','自吹自擂，吹嘘，夸耀拥有（值得自豪的东西）夸耀','uk :bəʊst, us :boʊst','[He didn t talk about his exam results in case people thought he was boasting. \n 他没有谈论自己的考试成绩，以免让别人以为他在自我吹嘘。 \n, Parents enjoy boasting about their children s achievements. \n 父母喜欢夸耀子女所取得的成绩。 \n, [ + that ] \n They boasted that they had never lost a single game. \n 他们夸口说从来没有输过一场比赛。 \n, Ireland boasts beautiful beaches, great restaurants, and friendly locals. \n 爱尔兰拥有美丽的海滩、很棒的餐馆和友好的当地人。 \n, [ + that ] \n It is her proud boast that she has never missed a single episode of the show. \n 她骄傲地夸口说这个肥皂剧她从未漏看过一集。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukblu/ukblunt027.mp3'),('boll-weevil','象鼻象鼻虫','Xiàng bí xiàng bí chóng','\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=boll-weevil&tl=ja&tk=378164.258368&client=webapp&prev=input'),('bookcase','书架；书橱','uk :ˈbʊk.keɪs, us :ˈbʊk.keɪs','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboo/ukbookb005.mp3'),('bosom','（女人的）乳房前胸；（尤指）胸怀，内心（女人）乳房丰满的','uk :ˈbʊz.əm, us :ˈbʊz.əm','[a large/ample bosom \n 大／丰满的乳房 \n, She held him tightly to her bosom. \n 她把他紧紧地拥在胸前。 \n, A dark jealousy stirred in his bosom. \n 他内心生出一阵恶毒的嫉妒。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbor/ukborin014.mp3'),('bourgeois','中产阶级的；追求物质享受的；平庸粗俗的','uk :ˈbɔːʒ.wɑː, us :ˈbʊrʒ.wɑː',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbou/ukbount005.mp3'),('bowl','碗；钵（物体的）碗状部分圆形运动场；圆形露天剧场草地滚木球戏（草地滚木球戏中所用的）木球；（保龄球运动中所用的）圆球（美国）美式橄榄球季后赛（在游戏中）滚动球把（球）投给击球员，投（球）','uk :bəʊl, us :boʊl','[a soup/cereal/salad/sugar bowl \n 汤碗／麦片粥碗／色拉钵／糖钵 \n, a bowl of soup/rice/porridge \n 一碗汤／米饭／粥 \n, She eats a bowl (= the contents of a bowl) of cereal every morning. \n 她每天早上吃一碗麦片粥。 \n, Sift the flour and baking powder into a mixing bowl. \n 将面粉和发酵粉筛进搅拌钵里。 \n, K \n Just put the dirty dishes in the washing-up bowl, and I ll do them later. \n 将脏碟子放进洗碗盆好了，我一会儿再洗。 \n, The toilet bowl was cracked and stained, and the walls were covered in mould. \n 抽水马桶破裂了，污迹斑斑，四周墙上到处都是霉点。 \n, the Hollywood Bowl \n 好莱坞露天剧场 \n, Bowls is one of the most popular sports in the UK . \n 草地滚球是英国最流行的运动之一。 \n, Pringle was tired after bowling for an hour. \n 投了一小时球后普林格尔累了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukboe/ukboer_020.mp3'),('breach','破坏，违犯；违反，不履行扰乱治安（行为）违反（法律或规章）（攻击墙或防御工事时打出的）缺口破坏，违犯；违反，不履行（尤指为从背后突袭）在…上打开缺口','uk :briːtʃ, us :briːtʃ','[They felt that our discussions with other companies constituted a breach of/in our agreement. \n 他们认为我们与别的公司谈判违反了我们之间的协定。 \n, He was sued for breach of contract. \n 他因为违反合同而被起诉。 \n, There have been serious security breaches (= breaks in our security system). \n 安全体系出了大问题。 \n, The theatre was in breach of the safety laws for having no fire doors. \n 由于没有消防门，这家剧院违反了安全法规。 \n, A cannon ball had made a breach in their castle walls. \n 一颗炮弹在他们城堡的墙上打出了一个缺口。 \n, They breached the agreement they had made with their employer. \n 他们违反了曾与雇主达成的协议。 \n, Their defences were easily breached. \n 他们的防线轻而易举就被突破了。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbra/ukbraw_013.mp3'),('briefly','短暂地；简短地简言之，一言以蔽之','uk :ˈbriːf.li, us :ˈbriːf.li','[We chatted briefly about the weather. \n 我们聊了几句天气。 \n, Briefly, the company needs to cut its expenditure. \n 简言之，公司需要缩减开支。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbre/ukbrew_028.mp3'),('bucket','（有提梁的）桶','uk :ˈbʌk.ɪt, us :ˈbʌk.ɪt','[Armed with a bucket and a mop, I started washing the floor. \n 提着桶和拖把，我开始拖地板。 \n, K \n I took my two-year-old nephew down to the beach with his bucket and spade. \n 我带两岁的小外甥去海滩，拿着他的小桶和铲子。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbru/ukbrusq022.mp3'),('bust','（女子的）胸部，胸围半身像逮捕；搜捕击碎；打破；弄坏逮捕；突击搜查（建筑物等）并逮捕疑犯坏的，损坏的破产','uk :bʌst, us :bʌst','[I couldn t find any blouses in my bust size. \n 我找不到适合我胸围的衬衫。 \n, There was a bust of Mahler on his desk. \n 他书桌上有一尊马勒的半身像。 \n, In their latest drugs bust police entered a warehouse where cocaine dealers were meeting. \n 在最近的毒品搜捕行动中，警方突袭了一个可卡因毒贩正在进行交易的仓库。 \n, Oh no! I bust his MP3 player. \n 噢，不好！我弄坏了他的MP3播放机。 \n, The police busted him because they think he s involved with a terrorist group. \n 警方认为他与恐怖团伙有牵连而逮捕了他。 \n, I think my watch is bust. \n 我想我的表坏了。 \n, More than 20 companies in the district went bust during the last three months. \n 过去的3个月里这一地区有超过20家公司破产。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbus/ukbushr012.mp3'),('cabbie','出租车司机，计程车司机','uk :ˈkæb.i, us :ˈkæb.i','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta013.mp3'),('cabinet','内阁贮藏柜；陈列柜；橱柜','uk :ˈkæb.ɪ.nət, us :ˈkæb.ən.ət','[The Cabinet meet/meets every Thursday. \n 内阁成员每周四开会。 \n, The President is completing the selection of his new Cabinet. \n 首相已宣布新内阁名单。 \n, a cabinet post \n 内阁大臣 \n, K \n a cabinet reshuffle (= changes in the Cabinet). \n 内阁改组 \n, K \n a cabinet minister \n 内阁部长 \n, Valuable pieces of china were on display in a glass-fronted cabinet. \n 贵重瓷器陈列在正面是玻璃的柜子里。 \n, a bathroom/filing cabinet \n 浴室／文件柜 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukb/ukbys/ukbysta017.mp3'),('campus','（大学）校园，校区','uk :ˈkæm.pəs, us :ˈkæm.pəs','[There s accommodation for about five hundred students on campus. \n 校区内可供约500名学生住宿。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcam/ukcambo029.mp3'),('capital market','资本市场','Zīběn shìchǎng','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=capital market&tl=ja&tk=508598.128706&client=webapp&prev=input'),('capricious','反复无常的','uk :kəˈprɪʃ.əs, us :kəˈprɪʃ.əs','[a capricious child \n 任性的小孩 \n, He was a cruel and capricious tyrant. \n 他是个残忍而又反复无常的暴君。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcap/ukcapit010.mp3'),('caption','（图书、杂志或报纸图片的）说明文字图片说明','uk :ˈkæp.ʃən, us :ˈkæp.ʃən','[The picture was captioned  Catherine Deneuve in Belle du Jour . \n 照片说明写道“凯瑟琳·德纳芙在《白日美人》中”。 \n, a captioned photograph \n 一幅带有文字说明的照片 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcap/ukcapit020.mp3'),('carnage','屠杀','Túshā','\n','2019-10-28',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=carnage &tl=ja&tk=460853.80961&client=webapp&prev=input'),('carve','（尤指在石头或木头上）雕刻把（熟肉）切成小片','uk :kɑːv, us :kɑːrv','[This totem pole is carved from/out of a single tree trunk. \n 这根图腾柱是由一整根树干雕刻而成的。 \n, He carved her name on a tree. \n 他将她的名字刻在了树上。 \n, Some of the tunnels in the cliff are natural, some were carved out (= cut into the rock) by soldiers for defensive purposes. \n 峭壁中的一些隧道是天然形成的，一些是士兵们在石头上开凿出来用于防御的。 \n, Would you like me to carve (the chicken)? \n 您要我（把鸡肉）切成小块吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcal/ukcalip022.mp3'),('catastrophic','严重的破坏','uk :ˌkæt.əˈstrɒf.ɪk, us :ˌkæt̬.əˈstrɑː.fɪk','[n unchecked increase in the use of fossil fuels could have catastrophic results for the planet.\n, A catastrophic storm made landfall on US soil.\n, he had to put her catastrophic Olympic performance out of her mind.\n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcas/ukcaste026.mp3'),('cathartic','解气','uk :kəˈθɑː.tɪk, us :kəˈθɑːr.tɪk','[ cathartic experience\n, I find it very cathartic to dance. \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcat/ukcatch021.mp3'),('characteristic','特色，特点，特征特有的，典型的','uk :ˌkær.ək.təˈrɪs.tɪk, us :ˌker.ək.təˈrɪs.tɪk','[Unfortunately a big nose is a family characteristic. \n 不幸的是，大鼻子是家族特征。 \n, Sentimentality seems a characteristic of all the writers of that period. \n 多愁善感似乎是那个时期所有作家的特征。 \n, The male bird displays (= has) several characteristics which distinguish him from the female. \n 雄鸟有几个有别于雌鸟的特征。 \n, With the hospitality so characteristic of these people, they opened their house to over 50 guests. \n 这些人生性好客，他们敞开家门接待了五十多位客人。 \n, She behaved with characteristic dignity. \n 她表现出自己特有的尊严。 \n, The creamy richness is characteristic of the cheese from this region. \n 奶味浓郁是该地区出产的奶酪的特色。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcha/ukchaot022.mp3'),('chewing','咀嚼；嚼碎（尤指为品尝味道而）嚼，咬嚼，咀嚼咀嚼物（越嚼越软的）硬糖；口香糖','uk :tʃuː, us :tʃuː','[This meat is difficult to chew. \n 这肉很难嚼。 \n, You don t chew your food enough - that s why you get indigestion. \n 你没把食物嚼烂——这就是你消化不良的原因。 \n, Would you like some gum to chew? \n 你想吃口香糖吗？ \n, She gave the children some sweets to chew (on) during the long car journey. \n 在漫长的汽车旅行途中，她给了孩子们些糖果嚼着吃。 \n, She sat in the dentist s waiting room, nervously chewing (at) (= biting) her nails. \n 她坐在牙医的候诊室里，紧张地咬着指甲。 \n, dog chews \n 狗咬胶 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukche/ukchess007.mp3'),('chick','雏鸟，幼鸟；（尤指）小鸡（冒犯性用语）女孩；少女；小妞儿','uk :tʃɪk, us :tʃɪk','[]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukche/ukchess017.mp3'),('chore','日常琐事；杂务；乏味的例行工作','uk :tʃɔːr, us :tʃɔːr','[I\'ll go shopping when I\'ve done my chores (= done the jobs in or around the house). \n 我把家务琐事干完后要去购物。 \n, I find writing reports a real chore (= very boring). \n 我觉得写报告真是件烦人的事。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcho/ukchora003.mp3'),('circumstance','条件，情况；情形，形势无法控制的因素；客观环境；命运经济状况','uk :ˈsɜː.kəm.stɑːns, us :ˈsɝː.kəm.stæns','[I think she coped very well under the circumstances. \n 我觉得在那种情况下她处理得很不错。 \n, Obviously we can\'t deal with the problem until we know all the circumstances. \n 显然，我们只有了解全部情况后才能处理这问题。 \n, She died in suspicious circumstances. \n 她死得很蹊跷。 \n, We oppose capital punishment in/under any circumstances. \n 无论在什么情况下，我们都不赞成死刑。 \n, Under no circumstances should you (= you should not) approach the man. \n 你无论如何都不应该联系那个男人。 \n, The meeting has been cancelled due to circumstances beyond our control. \n 会议因不可控情况的出现而被取消了。 \n, They were victims of circumstance. \n 他们是客观环境的牺牲品。 \n, We were obliged to go by force of circumstance. \n 形势所迫，我们不得不走。 \n, Grants are available depending on your circumstances. \n 视经济状况，符合条件可获得助学金。 \n, By now she was alone and living in reduced circumstances (= with little money). \n 现在她孤单一人，生活拮据。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcin/ukcinna026.mp3'),('classier','流行的；时髦的；豪华的','uk :ˈklɑː.si, us :ˈklæs.i','[That s one classy vehicle you ve got there. \n 你那辆车真是太气派了。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcla/ukclass004.mp3'),('clatter','（使）发出响亮的撞击声；（使）哐啷作响','uk :ˈklæt.ər, us :ˈklæt̬.ɚ','[Don t clatter the dishes - you ll wake the baby up. \n 别把碗碟碰得叮当响——会把宝宝吵醒的。 \n, He was clattering away at his keyboard. \n 他在键盘上咔嗒咔嗒打东西。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcla/ukclass005.mp3'),('clown','丑角，小丑（常指故意）出洋相的人；愚蠢可笑的人扮小丑；出洋相；逗笑','uk :klaʊn, us :klaʊn','[Left alone, the class threw books, pulled faces, and generally clowned around. \n 由于没有人管，班上的学生扔书本，扮鬼脸，简直胡闹成一片。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukclo/ukclosu015.mp3'),('coinage','货币系统，货币制度新造的词（语）；新词语的创造','uk :ˈkɔɪ.nɪdʒ, us :ˈkɔɪ.nɪdʒ','[decimal coinage \n 十进位币制 \n, The expression  boy band  is a 1990s coinage. \n boy band（男孩乐队）是20世纪90年代的新词语。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcoh/ukcohab016.mp3'),('colonist','殖民地居民；殖民地移民；殖民地开拓者','uk :ˈkɒl.ə.nist, us :ˈkɑː.lə.nist','[]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01677.mp3'),('colossal','巨大的，庞大的','uk :kəˈlɒs.əl, us :kəˈlɑː.səl','[In the centre of the hall stood a colossal wooden statue, decorated in ivory and gold. \n 大厅中央矗立着一尊用象牙和金子装饰的木质巨型雕像。 \n, They were asking a colossal amount of money for the house. \n 他们对这房子漫天要价。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcol/ukcolor003.mp3'),('commanding height','制高点','Zhǐlìng gāodù','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q= commanding height&tl=ja&tk=509866.127966&client=webapp&prev=input'),('commercial','商业的；商务的；贸易的（唱片、电影、书等）商业化的，以营利为目的的（产品）商品化的（广播或电视）商业性的，靠广告收入维持的（电视或广播里的）商业广告','uk :kəˈmɜː.ʃəl, us :kəˈmɝː.ʃəl','[a commercial organization/venture/success \n 商业组织／企业／成功 \n, commercial law \n 商法 \n, The commercial future of the company looks very promising. \n 这家公司的商业前景看起来非常光明。 \n, a commercial break \n 插播广告 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcomma024.mp3'),('commission','（正式地）安排…做，委托…做委任（或任命）…为军官（负责调查问题真相或原因的）委员会佣金；提成；回扣委托；请求犯罪军官的职务（或职权）','uk :kəˈmɪʃ.ən, us :kəˈmɪʃ.ən','[The newspaper commissioned a series of articles on the worst excesses of the fashion industry. \n 报社请人撰写了一系列针砭时装业极端倾向的文章。 \n, She\'s commissioned an artist to paint her portrait. \n 她请了一位艺术家为她画肖像。 \n, Grandfather was commissioned as Group Captain in the RAF just before the war. \n 就在战争爆发前夕祖父被任命为皇家空军上校。 \n, a commission on alcohol abuse/racial tension \n 酗酒问题／种族间紧张关系调查委员会 \n, The government has set up/established a commission to investigate the problem of inner city violence. \n 政府设立了专门委员会来调查市中心区的暴力问题。 \n, Is she paid a regular wage or is it on/by commission only? \n 她拿正式工资还是只拿提成？ \n, She gets a 15 percent commission on every machine she sells. \n 她每卖出一台机器就拿15%的提成。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n She\'s just got a commission to paint Sir Ellis Pike\'s wife. \n 她刚刚受托为埃利斯‧帕克爵士的夫人画像。 \n, Do you do/take commissions? \n 你接受委托吗？ \n, the commission of the crime/offence/murder \n 犯罪／犯法／犯杀人罪 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcom/ukcommi006.mp3'),('competitive edge','竞争优势','Jìngzhēng yōushì','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=competitive edge&tl=ja&tk=177902.295578&client=webapp&prev=input'),('conduct','组织；实施；进行；处理（尤指在公共或正式场合中）举止，表现；为人引导；带领；指引；给…带路为…导游，带（游客）游览指挥（合唱团、乐队等）传导（电或热）行为，举止；表现；为人组织方式；实施方式','uk :kənˈdʌkt, us :kənˈdʌkt','[We are conducting a survey to find out what our customers think of their local bus service. \n 我们正在进行一项调查，了解顾客对当地公交服务系统的看法。 \n, The experiments were conducted by scientists in New York. \n 这些实验是科学家在纽约做的。 \n, How you choose to conduct your private life is your own business! \n 你选择怎么过你的私生活是你自己的事！ \n, How should I conduct myself at these dinners? I know nothing about etiquette. \n 我在这类晚宴上该怎样做到举止得体呢？对于礼仪我可是一窍不通。 \n, May I conduct you to your table, sir, or would you prefer to have a drink at the bar first? \n 先生，我带您去餐桌呢，还是您先在吧台喝上一杯？ \n, The protesters were conducted from the courtroom by two police officers. \n 抗议者被两名警察带出了法庭。 \n, A guide conducts tours of the cathedral every afternoon at 2.00. \n 每天下午2点一位导游会带游客参观大教堂。 \n, a conducted tour of the palace \n 有导游陪同的宫殿游 \n, The orchestra was conducted by Mira Shapur. \n 管弦乐队由米拉‧沙普尔指挥。 \n, Who\'s conducting at tonight\'s concert? \n 今晚的音乐会谁担任指挥？ \n, Copper conducts electricity, but plastic does not. \n 铜导电，但塑料不导电。 \n, bad/excellent/disgraceful conduct \n 糟糕的／得体的／丢脸的举止 \n, The club has a strict code (= set of rules) of conduct. \n 该俱乐部有严格的行为准则。 \n, He was criticized for his conduct of the inquiry. \n 他组织这次调查的方式受到了批评。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconde029.mp3'),('conducted-away','排除在外','null','null\n','2019-12-03',1,1,0,'null'),('confirmatory','确切的','uk :kənˈfɜː.mə.tər.i, us :kənˈfɜ˞ː.mə.tɔːr.i','[nyone who tests positive with a rapid test must get a confirmatory blood test.\n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318ukconf0346.mp3'),('confrontation','对抗；冲突；对峙；争论','uk :ˌkɒn.frʌnˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.frənˈteɪ.ʃən','[Some couples seem to like confrontation, but Josh and I hardly ever argue. \n 有的夫妻似乎很喜欢争吵，我跟乔希却几乎没有吵过嘴。 \n, There were violent confrontations between police and demonstrators. \n 警察和示威者之间发生了激烈的冲突。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfi026.mp3'),('congregate','聚集，集合','uk :ˈkɒŋ.ɡrɪ.ɡeɪt, us :ˈkɑːŋ.ɡrə.ɡeɪt','[A crowd congregated around the entrance to the theatre, hoping to catch a glimpse of the stars of the show. \n 一群人聚集在戏院门口，希望能看一眼演出的明星。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconfu019.mp3'),('consequent','作为结果的；随之而来的；由此引起的','uk :ˈkɒn.sɪ.kwənt, us :ˈkɑːn.sə.kwənt','[Our use of harmful chemicals and the consequent damage to the environment is a very serious matter. \n 我们使用有害化学物品且因此对环境造成了破坏，这是件非常严重的事情。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsc020.mp3'),('constitution','宪法；章程体质，体格组成；构成；结构；构造','uk :ˌkɒn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən, us :ˌkɑːn.stəˈtuː.ʃən',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsp021.mp3'),('constitutional','宪法（或章程）允许的，符合宪法（或章程）的体质的，体格的健身散步','uk :ˌkɒn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən.əl, us :ˌkɑːn.stəˈtuː.ʃən.əl',NULL,'2019-10-03',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconsp022.mp3'),('contingency','可能发生的事；意外事件，不测事件','uk :kənˈtɪn.dʒən.si, us :kənˈtɪn.dʒən.si','[You must be able to deal with all possible contingencies. \n 你必须能应付一切可能发生的意外事件。 \n, Have you made any contingency plans? \n 你们制订应急方案了吗？ \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconte020.mp3'),('convey','表达，传达（思想、感情或想法）运送，运输','uk :kənˈveɪ, us :kənˈveɪ','[His poetry conveys a great sense of religious devotion. \n 他的诗歌表达了献身宗教的强烈感情。 \n, Please convey our condolences to the family. \n 请向家人转达我们的哀思。 \n, [ + question word ] \n I tried to convey in my speech how grateful we all were for his help. \n 在发言中，我竭力地表达我们大家对他所给予帮助的感激之情。 \n, You don t want to convey the impression that we re not interested. \n 你不想给人留下我们不感兴趣的印象吧。 \n, The goods are usually conveyed by rail. \n 这种货物通常通过铁路运输。 \n, Could you convey a message to Mr Merrick for me, please? \n 你能替我给梅里克先生传个口信吗？ \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve003.mp3'),('convincing','令人信服的；有说服力的令人心悦诚服的胜利，大比分获胜','uk :kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ, us :kənˈvɪn.sɪŋ','[a convincing argument/explanation \n 令人信服的论据／解释 \n, convincing evidence \n 确凿的证据 \n, The end of the book wasn\'t very convincing. \n 这本书的结局难以令人信服。 \n, They won a convincing victory. \n 他们大比分获胜。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcon/ukconve013.mp3'),('cotton','棉，棉花棉线；棉布（通常用于清洁皮肤的）药棉，脱脂棉','uk :ˈkɒt.ən, us :ˈkɑː.t̬ən','[a bale of cotton \n 一大包棉花 \n, a shirt made of pure cotton \n 纯棉衬衫 \n, She looked pretty in a simple cotton dress. \n 她穿着朴素的棉布连衣裙，看上去很漂亮。 \n, K \n a reel of cotton (= thread) \n 一卷棉线 \n, cotton pads \n 化妆棉 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcos/ukcossa021.mp3'),('coward','胆小鬼，懦夫','uk :ˈkaʊ.əd, us :ˈkaʊ.ɚd','[They branded her a coward for informing on her colleagues during the interrogation. \n 她在审讯中告发了同事，因此被视为懦夫。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcov/ukcover012.mp3'),('creep','（通常指为避免注意而）缓慢行进，悄悄移动，潜行谄媚者，奴颜婢膝者，阿谀奉承者讨厌鬼，令人恶心的人（尤指男人）使…毛骨悚然；使…紧张害怕','uk :kriːp, us :kriːp','[She turned off the light and crept through the door. \n 她关上灯，悄悄溜出门。 \n, Someone was creeping around outside my window. \n 有人在我的窗户外蹑手蹑脚地走动。 \n, The spider crept up the wall. \n 蜘蛛缓缓地爬上墙。 \n, The traffic was creeping along at a snail s pace. \n 车辆如蜗牛般缓慢移动。 \n, Making coffee for the boss again? You creep! \n 又在给老板冲咖啡？你这个马屁精！ \n, He was such a creep - he was always staring at me in the canteen. \n 他真是个讨厌鬼——在饭厅里他老盯着我看。 \n, [ as form of address ] \n Leave me alone, creep! \n 让我一个人呆一会儿，你这个讨厌鬼！ \n, Living next to a graveyard would give me the creeps. \n 住在墓地旁边会令我毛骨悚然。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcre/ukcreed002.mp3'),('crisis','危机，极其困难的时期紧要关头，危急时刻（疾病的）危险期，关键期信任危机','uk :ˈkraɪ.sɪs, us :ˈkraɪ.sɪs',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp003.mp3'),('crisp','脆的；易碎的（糕点、饼干等食物）酥脆的（蔬果）新鲜爽脆的，脆生生的（纸或布）挺括的，平展的（声音或形象）清晰明了的（说话、写作或行为）干脆利落的，利索的，明快的（天气）干冷的，晴冷的（空气）清爽的，凉爽的油炸薯片酥皮水果甜点心','uk :krɪsp, us :krɪsp','[a crisp apple \n 脆生生的苹果 \n, a crisp new £5 note/a crisp white tablecloth \n 平展簇新的5英镑钞票／平展的白色桌布 \n, The sound from the new speakers is very crisp. \n 新扬声器的声音非常清晰。 \n, a crisp reply \n 干脆利落的回答 \n, a crisp, efficient manner \n 举止利落干练 \n, a wonderful crisp spring morning \n 一个晴爽的春日清晨 \n, I breathed in deeply the crisp mountain air. \n 我深深地吸了口山间清爽的空气。 \n, a packet of salt and vinegar crisps \n 一袋盐醋薯片 \n, apple crisp \n 酥皮苹果甜点 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcri/ukcripp004.mp3'),('crossword','纵横填字游戏','uk :ˈkrɒs.wɜːd, us :ˈkrɑːs.wɝːd','[I do the Times crossword every morning. \n 我每天早上都要做《泰晤士报》上的填字游戏。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcross018.mp3'),('crowd','>人群；群众>（有共同爱好的）一帮朋友，一伙人，一群人>挤；靠近；盯着','uk :>kraʊd, us :>kraʊd',NULL,'2019-09-25',0,4,0,NULL),('crucial','至关重要的；关键的；决定性的','uk :ˈkruː.ʃəl, us :ˈkruː.ʃəl','[a crucial decision/question \n 至关重要的决定／问题 \n, Her work has been crucial to the project\'s success. \n 她的工作对于这个项目的成功至关重要。 \n, [ + that ] \n It is crucial that the problem is tackled immediately. \n 关键是要马上着手处理这一问题。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcro/ukcrowe004.mp3'),('curator','（博物馆、图书馆等的）馆长','uk :kjʊˈreɪ.tər, us :kjɝːˈeɪ.t̬ɚ',NULL,'2019-10-03',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcun/ukcunt_019.mp3'),('customs-union','关税同盟','null','null\n','2019-12-03',0,2,0,'null'),('cと、熱心に仕事に取り組んでいるように見えます。','有了c，看来他正在努力。',' nesshin ni shigoto ni torikunde iru yō ni miemasu.','\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=cと、熱心に仕事に取り組んでいるように見えます。&tl=ja&tk=912580.776368&client=webapp&prev=input'),('dame','女人（童话剧中通常由男人扮演的）老年女丑角，滑稽老太婆（英国授予有贡献的女性的荣誉称号）女爵士；有女爵士头衔的女性','uk :deɪm, us :deɪm','[Dame Judy Dench \n 朱迪‧登奇女爵士 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdag/ukdagoe026.mp3'),('dapper','（男子）穿着考究的，衣冠楚楚的','uk :ˈdæp.ər, us :ˈdæp.ɚ','[Hercule Poirot is the dapper detective of the Agatha Christie novels. \n 赫尔克里‧波洛就是阿加莎‧克里斯蒂小说中那位衣冠楚楚的侦探。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdam/ukdamne030.mp3'),('debt','借款，欠款；债务','uk :det, us :det','[He managed to pay off his debts in two years. \n 他设法在两年内还清了债务。 \n, The company ran up huge debts. \n 公司很快就负债累累。 \n, They are in debt to (= owe money to) the bank. \n 他们欠银行的钱。 \n, He got into debt (= borrowed money) after he lost his job. \n 他失业后开始举债。 \n, The company is deep in debt (= owes a lot of money). \n 公司已经债台高筑。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath023.mp3'),('decade','十年；年代','uk :ˈdek.eɪd, us :ˈdek.eɪd','[]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdea/ukdeath030.mp3'),('decorate','装饰，装点，打扮粉刷；（给…）贴壁纸（尤指授予奖章以）嘉奖，表彰','uk :ˈdek.ə.reɪt, us :ˈdek.ər.eɪt','[They decorated the wedding car with ribbons and flowers. \n 他们用彩带和鲜花装点婚车。 \n, We re going to decorate the kitchen next week. \n 我们下周要粉刷厨房。 \n, I hate the smell of paint when I m decorating. \n 我刷墙时很讨厌油漆味儿。 \n, They were decorated for their part in the rescue. \n 他们因在此次救援行动中的表现而受到嘉奖。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdec/ukdecod014.mp3'),('defect','缺点；缺陷；瑕疵生理缺陷；生理障碍（尤指为加入敌对国家、政党等）脱离，退出，叛逃','uk :ˈdiː.fekt, us :ˈdiː.fekt',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdef/ukdefec001.mp3'),('delicate','脆弱的；娇嫩的需要小心处理的微妙的形势（问题，时刻等）精细的，精密的柔和的；轻柔的；清淡的纤细的，细长的','uk :ˈdel.ɪ.kət, us :ˈdel.ə.kət','[Peaches have delicate skins which are easily bruised. \n 桃子的表皮很娇嫩，容易碰伤。 \n, Delicate plants need to be kept in a greenhouse during the winter. \n 娇贵的植物需要在温室里过冬。 \n, delicate china \n 易碎的瓷器 \n, Molly s health has always been delicate (= she gets sick easily). \n 莫莉的身体一直都很娇弱。 \n, Repairing damaged nerves is a very delicate operation/process. \n 修复受损神经的手术／过程需要非常小心谨慎。 \n, I need to speak to you about a delicate matter. \n 我要跟你谈一件很棘手的事情。 \n, The pay negotiations have reached a delicate point/stage. \n 工资谈判已经到了微妙的关头／阶段。 \n, Teachers need to strike a delicate (= carefully achieved) balance between instructing their students and letting them discover things for themselves. \n 教师需要在向学生传授知识和引导学生自己去探索之间找到一个微妙的平衡点。 \n, Weather-forecasters have extremely delicate equipment which helps them predict what the weather is going to be like. \n 气象预报人员使用非常精密的设备来帮助他们预测天气变化。 \n, a rose with a delicate scent \n 散发清香的玫瑰 \n, a delicate shade of pink \n 柔和的粉色 \n, We chose a delicate floral pattern for our bedroom curtains. \n 我们为卧室选了一种花色图案非常淡雅的窗帘。 \n, She folded her delicate hands on the table. \n 她纤纤十指交叉着放在桌上。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdej/ukdejur023.mp3'),('delta','三角洲（希腊语字母表的第四个字母）','uk :ˈdel.tə, us :ˈdel.t̬ə','[the Mississippi delta \n 密西西比河三角洲 \n, the delta of the Nile \n 尼罗河三角洲 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdel/ukdelig020.mp3'),('demerit','缺陷；劣势（尤指学校给学生的）记过，过失分','uk :ˌdiːˈmer.ɪt, us :ˌdiːˈmer.ɪt','[We need to consider the merits and demerits of the plan. \n 我们需要考虑该计划的优缺点。 \n, She got three demerits for lateness on this term s report. \n 她因迟到在本学期总评中被记过3次。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemag017.mp3'),('demonstrator','展示者，演示者，示范者示威者，游行者','uk :ˈdem.ən.streɪ.tər, us :ˈdem.ən.streɪ.t̬ɚ','[A demonstrator was showing customers how the food processor worked. \n 一个人在向顾客演示如何使用食品加工器。 \n, Police arrested several of the demonstrators. \n 警察逮捕了数名示威者。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdem/ukdemoc026.mp3'),('derivative','缺乏独创性的；模仿的衍生物，派生物；派生词金融衍生产品','uk :dɪˈrɪv.ə.tɪv, us :dɪˈrɪv.ə.t̬ɪv','[His painting/style is very derivative. \n 他的油画／风格有很重的模仿痕迹。 \n,  Detestable  is a derivative of  detest . \n detestable 这个词是从 detest 派生而来的。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg011.mp3'),('derive','从…中得到，从…中获得','uk :dɪˈraɪv, us :dɪˈraɪv','[The institute derives all its money from foreign investments. \n 该机构的资金均来自于国外投资。 \n, She derives great pleasure/satisfaction from playing the violin. \n 拉小提琴能让她获得极大的乐趣／满足。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg013.mp3'),('detective','侦探警探（用于某些级别的警察头衔）','uk :dɪˈtek.tɪv, us :dɪˈtek.tɪv','[a private detective \n 私家侦探 \n, detective stories \n 侦探故事 \n, Detective Sergeant Lewis \n 刘易斯探长 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetai008.mp3'),('detest','憎恨；厌恶，讨厌','uk :dɪˈtest, us :dɪˈtest','[I detest any kind of cruelty. \n 我厌恶任何形式的残暴。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I detest having to get up when it\'s dark outside. \n 我讨厌天不亮就得起床。 \n, her detested older brother \n 她那令人讨厌的哥哥 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetai023.mp3'),('devastate','摧毁；毁灭使极为震惊；使极为烦乱','uk :ˈdev.ə.steɪt, us :ˈdev.ə.steɪt',NULL,'2019-10-03',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdet/ukdetou015.mp3'),('devotee','（狂热的）崇拜者，爱好者','uk :ˌdev.əˈtiː, us :ˌdev.əˈtiː','[He is a great devotee of the prime minister. \n 他是首相的狂热崇拜者。 \n, devotees of golf \n 高尔夫球爱好者 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdev/ukdevil015.mp3'),('dial','拨号，按号码表盘，仪表盘旋钮，调节器（老式电话机的）拨号盘','uk :ˈdaɪ.əl, us :ˈdaɪ.əl','[Can I dial this number direct, or do I have to go through the operator? \n 我可以直接拨这个号码还是需要通过话务员接转？ \n, Dial 0 for the switchboard. \n 总机拨0。 \n, Can you read what it says on the dial? \n 你能读出仪表盘上的读数吗？ \n, The dial of/on his watch had a picture of Mickey Mouse on it. \n 他手表的表盘上有一个米老鼠的图案。 \n, You turn this dial to find a different radio station. \n 转动这个旋钮可选择不同的广播电台。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdex/ukdextr019.mp3'),('dimly','昏暗的','uk :ˈdɪm.li, us :ˈdɪm.li','[he room was dimly lit.\n, The February sun shone dimly.\n,  dimly remembered reading the book a few years before.\n, They were only dimly aware of the telephone ringing.\n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdig/ukdigs_029.mp3'),('dimmer','亮度调节器','uk :ˈdɪm.ər, us :ˈdɪm.ɚ','[]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/uka32/uka32549.mp3'),('disguise','给…化装，给…乔装打扮；将…伪装起来掩饰，隐藏（观点、感受等）化装用具（服饰）；用于伪装的东西伪装，化装','uk :dɪsˈɡaɪz, us :dɪsˈɡaɪz','[He disguised himself by wearing a false beard. \n 他粘上假胡须伪装自己。 \n, Minor skin imperfections can usually be disguised with a spot of make-up. \n 微小的皮肤瑕疵通常可以用化妆品来掩盖。 \n, We tried to disguise the fact that it was just a school hall by putting up coloured lights and balloons. \n 我们挂上彩灯和气球，不想让人看出这里实际上只是一个学校礼堂。 \n, I couldn t disguise my disappointment. \n 我无法掩饰自己的失望。 \n, He put on a large hat and glasses as a disguise and hoped no one would recognize him. \n 他戴上大帽子和眼镜来伪装自己，希望没人会认出他来。 \n, She usually goes out in disguise to avoid being bothered by the public. \n 她外出时通常都要化装，以免受到公众的打扰。 \n, He claims that most Western aid to the Third World is just colonialism in disguise. \n 他说西方给第三世界提供的援助大多只是变相的殖民主义行为。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisgu001.mp3'),('disruption','分裂','uk :dɪsˈrʌpʃən, us :','[t would cause a tremendous disruption to our work schedule to install a different computer system.\n, A crackdown on illegal-immigrant hiring could create widespread workplace disruptions.\n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisre010.mp3'),('dissent','（尤指对正式建议、计划或普遍看法的）不同意，异议不服裁判不同意，持有异议','uk :dɪˈsent, us :dɪˈsent',NULL,'2019-10-03',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukder/ukdereg029.mp3'),('dissolution','（官方组织的）解散；（法律合约的）解除','uk :ˌdɪs.əˈluː.ʃən, us :ˌdɪs.əˈluː.ʃən',NULL,'2019-10-03',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdissi007.mp3'),('distinguishable','易分辨的','uk :dɪˈstɪŋ.ɡwɪ.ʃə.bəl, us :dɪˈstɪŋ.ɡwɪ.ʃə.bəl','[here are at least 20 distinguishable dialects of the language just on the south island.\n, His days were barely distinguishable from one another. \n,  few words were distinguishable among the slurred muttering.\n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisti002.mp3'),('dithering','犹豫，踌躇对…感到紧张（或激动、困惑等）','uk :ˈdɪð.ər, us :ˈdɪð.ɚ','[Stop dithering and choose which one you want! \n 别犹豫了，赶快决定你想要哪个！ \n, She\'s still dithering over whether to accept the job she\'s just been offered. \n 她还在犹豫要不要接受刚刚给她的那份工作。 \n, Gideon is in a bit of a dither about what to wear for the interview. \n 吉迪恩紧张得有些不知穿什么衣服去参加面试才好。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdis/ukdisun006.mp3'),('dorm','（尤指寄宿学校或大学的）宿舍（学院或大学的）学生宿舍楼','uk :dɔːm, us :dɔːrm','[The hostel has single-sex dorms.\n, Smoking is not permitted in college dorms.\n, My mom and I were buying things for my dorm room.\n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukd/ukdop/ukdopie006.mp3'),('drawer','抽屉（同underpants）','uk :drɔːr, us :drɑː','[I keep my socks in the bottom drawer. \n 我把袜子放在最下面的抽屉里。 \n, He rummaged through his desk drawer trying to find a pen. \n 他翻遍书桌抽屉，想要找到一支笔。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/e/epd/epd31/epd31709.mp3'),('elaborate','精心计划（或制作）的；详尽的；复杂的详尽说明；阐述','uk :iˈlæb.ər.ət, us :iˈlæb.ɚ.ət','[You want a plain blouse to go with that skirt - nothing too elaborate. \n 你应该用一件样式简单的衬衫来配那条裙子，不要样式太复杂的。 \n, They re making the most elaborate preparations for the wedding. \n 他们正为婚礼做极为精心周到的准备。 \n, He came out with such an elaborate excuse that I didn t quite believe him. \n 他突然说了那么一大套理由，我不太相信他。 \n, The congresswoman said she was resigning, but refused to elaborate on her reasons for doing so. \n 这位国会女议员说她要辞职，但拒绝说明辞职的原因。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeig/ukeight014.mp3'),('elbow','肘；（衣服的）肘部用肘推；用肘挤开（为让某人注意或提醒某事而）用肘碰','uk :ˈel.bəʊ, us :ˈel.boʊ','[Her arm was bandaged from the elbow to the fingers. \n 她的胳膊从肘部一直到手指全缠上了绷带。 \n, The sleeve of his shirt was torn at the elbow. \n 他的衬衫的肘部被撕了个口子。 \n, He elbowed his way to the front of the crowd. \n 他挤到了人群的前边。 \n, They elbowed the onlookers aside. \n 他们把旁观者推到一边。 \n, She elbowed me in the ribs before I could say anything. \n 我还没开口呢，她就用胳膊肘在我肋部碰了一下。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeig/ukeight030.mp3'),('elite','（社会）上层集团；掌权人物；出类拔萃的人，精英（社会）上层集团的；掌权人物的；精英的','uk :iˈliːt, us :iˈliːt','[the country\'s educated elite \n 这个国家受过良好教育的精英 \n, a member of the elite \n 上层集团的一员 \n, isapproving \n A powerful and corrupt elite has bled this country dry. \n 该国专权腐败的权贵阶层榨干了人民的血汗。 \n, Elite troops were airlifted to the trouble zone. \n 精锐部队被空运到骚乱地区。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukeli/ukelimi005.mp3'),('eminent','显赫的；卓越的；著名的','uk :ˈem.ɪ.nənt, us :ˈem.ə.nənt',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukemb/ukembry021.mp3'),('encrust','cover or decorate (something) with a hard surface layer','/ɪnˈkrʌst,ɛnˈkrʌst/','null\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'null'),('entail','使必要；牵涉','uk :ɪnˈteɪl, us :ɪnˈteɪl','[Such a large investment inevitably entails some risk. \n 这样的巨额投资必然会有一定的风险。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n Repairing the roof will entail spending a lot of money. \n 修房顶免不了要花好多钱。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukens/ukensla007.mp3'),('episode','事件；（相关的）一连串事件；一段经历（尤指电视或广播节目的）一集，一节，片断','uk :ˈep.ɪ.səʊd, us :ˈep.ə.soʊd','[This latest episode in the fraud scandal has shocked a lot of people. \n 诈骗丑闻最新爆出的这一事件让很多人瞠目结舌。 \n, The drugs, the divorce, and the depression - it s an episode in his life that he wants to forget. \n 吸毒、离婚和消沉——这是他人生中不堪回首的一段经历。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukepe/ukepee_023.mp3'),('equity','（公司的）股本，股票值；股票资产净值公平；公正（英语国家的一种司法制度，允许在现存法律不适用时对案件作出公正判决的）衡平法','uk :ˈek.wɪ.ti, us :ˈek.wə.t̬i','[He sold his equity in the company last year. \n 他去年卖掉了这家公司的股票。 \n, The rights give holders the opportunity to purchase additional equity interests in the company at a big discount. \n 这些权利使得股票持有者有机会以很优惠的折扣价额外购买该公司股份。 \n, a society based on equity and social justice \n 建立在公平公正和社会正义基础之上的社会 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukequ/ukequip004.mp3'),('establishment','企业；机构；单位（尤指支持维持现状的）当权派，统治集团，权势集团建立；创立','uk :ɪˈstæb.lɪʃ.mənt, us :ɪˈstæb.lɪʃ.mənt',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukesq/ukesq__010.mp3'),('exemption','免税','uk :ɪɡˈzemp.ʃən, us :ɪɡˈzemp.ʃən','[andidates with a qualification in chemistry have exemption from this course.\n, Organizations may qualify for exemption from income tax if they operate exclusively as charities.\n,  U ] \n He was granted exemption from military service during World War II.\n,  C ] \n a tax exemption\n, xemption from sth \n Formula One was granted an exemption from a ban on tobacco advertising.\n, xemption from doing sth \n Can the parent company claim exemption from preparing a cash flow statement?\n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexc/ukexcre028.mp3'),('exert','运用；行使（权威、权力等）；施加（影响等）用力；尽力；努力','uk :ɪɡˈzɜːt, us :ɪɡˈzɝːt','[If you were to exert your influence they might change their decision. \n 如果你能施加你的影响，他们或许会改变决定。 \n, Some managers exert considerable pressure on their staff to work extra hours without being paid. \n 一些老板向员工施加巨大的压力迫使他们无偿加班。 \n, I was too tired to exert myself. \n 我太累了，心有余而力不足。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert001.mp3'),('exhibit','展出，展览；展示展品；展出物；陈列品（一批）展品，展览（法庭上出示的）证据，物证','uk :ɪɡˈzɪb.ɪt, us :ɪɡˈzɪb.ɪt','[He frequently exhibits at the art gallery. \n 他经常在艺术馆展出作品。 \n, In the summer the academy will exhibit several prints that are rarely seen. \n 该学会将于今年夏天对外展出几幅罕见的版画作品。 \n, He exhibited great self-control considering her rudeness. \n 她那么无礼，他表现出如此的克制力已很不错了。 \n, The museum has a fascinating collection of exhibits ranging from Iron Age pottery to Inuit clothing. \n 这个博物馆收藏的展品，从铁器时代的陶器，到因纽特人的衣物，丰富多彩，令人称奇。 \n, Let\'s go see the new dinosaur exhibit. \n 我们去看这个有关恐龙的新展览吧。 \n, Is exhibit C the weapon that you say was used? \n 物证C是不是你说的所使用的武器？ \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexe/ukexert016.mp3'),('expire','到期，期满；结束逝世，亡故','uk :ɪkˈspaɪər, us :ɪkˈspaɪr','[My passport expires next month. \n 我的护照下个月过期。 \n, The contract between the two companies will expire at the end of the year. \n 两公司之间的合同将在年底到期。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexper014.mp3'),('exploit','利用；开发；发挥（出于私利）利用；剥削不寻常的行为；英勇的行为；奇遇','uk :ɪkˈsplɔɪt, us :ɪkˈsplɔɪt','[We need to make sure that we exploit our resources as fully as possible. \n 我们需要确保尽可能充分利用资源。 \n, Laws exist to stop companies exploiting their employees. \n 法律规定禁止公司剥削其员工。 \n, She was telling me about her exploits while travelling around Africa. \n 她跟我讲述了她在非洲各地旅游时的奇遇。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukexp/ukexper030.mp3'),('extreme','极大的；极度的；极端的极严厉的；严重的；极糟的（信仰或政党）偏激的，过激的，极端的末端的，尽头的；（尤指）离中心最远的极度；极端（用于强调）极其，非常，极度极端；极端不同的事物','uk :ɪkˈstriːm, us :ɪkˈstriːm',NULL,'2019-09-25',1,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uke/ukext/ukextra024.mp3'),('fad','一时的风尚；短暂的狂热','uk :fæd, us :fæd','[the latest health fad \n 最新健康时尚 \n, K \n There was a fad for wearing ripped jeans a few years ago. \n 几年前有一阵子流行穿有洞的牛仔裤。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfac/ukfacin016.mp3'),('fade','（使）褪色；（使）变暗；（使）衰弱','uk :feɪd, us :feɪd','[If you hang your clothes out in the bright sun, they will fade. \n 衣服挂在光线强的地方晾晒会褪色。 \n, My suntan is already fading. \n 我晒黑的肤色已经开始变浅了。 \n, They arrived home just as the light was fading (= as it was getting dark). \n 天色变暗时，他们到家了。 \n, The sun had faded the blue walls. \n 太阳把蓝色的墙晒褪了色。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfac/ukfacin025.mp3'),('faint','微弱的；不清晰的；微小的根本不知道虚弱无力；感到眩晕；快要晕倒似的昏厥；晕倒昏厥；晕倒','uk :feɪnt, us :feɪnt','[a faint sound/noise/smell \n 微弱的声音／隐约的响声／淡淡的气味 \n, The lamp gave out a faint glow. \n 灯发出微弱的光。 \n, She gave me a faint smile of recognition. \n 她认出了我，冲我淡淡一笑。 \n, There s not the faintest hope of ever finding him. \n 没有丝毫找到他的希望。 \n, She bears a faint resemblance to my sister. \n 她和我姐姐长得有点儿像。 \n, I have a faint suspicion that you may be right! \n 我隐约觉得你可能是对的！ \n,  Is she going to stay?   I haven t the faintest idea.  \n “她要留下来吗？我一点儿也不知道。” \n, I don t have the faintest idea what you re talking about! \n 我根本不知道你在说什么！ \n, She felt faint with hunger. \n 她饿得头昏眼花。 \n, He faints at the sight of blood. \n 他一见血就晕。 \n, I nearly fainted in the heat. \n 我差点热晕过去。 \n, She took one look at the hypodermic needle and fainted (dead) away (= became unconscious immediately). \n 她一眼看到注射针头就昏了过去。 \n, On receiving the news, she fell into a dead faint. \n 听到消息，她昏死过去。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfag/ukfagge009.mp3'),('fanciful','空想的；想象的','uk :ˈfæn.sɪ.fəl, us :ˈfæn.sɪ.fəl','[He has some fanciful notion about converting one room of his apartment into a gallery. \n 他幻想把他公寓的一间房间改成画廊。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfal/ukfalsi023.mp3'),('fancy','想要；想做爱慕，喜欢自认为是；自命不凡想象；认为（表示惊讶）真想不到！装饰的；花哨的；繁复的昂贵的；豪华的一时的兴趣（或爱好）喜欢上，爱上吸引…，中…的意想象（力）','uk :ˈfæn.si, us :ˈfæn.si','[Do you fancy a drink this evening? \n 你今晚想喝一杯吗？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n I didn t fancy swimming in that water. \n 我不想在那水里游泳。 \n, He could tell she fancied him. \n 他看得出她喜欢他。 \n, That Dave really fancies himself, doesn t he? \n 那个戴夫挺自命不凡的，是吧？ \n, He fancies himself as a bit of a singer. \n 他认为自己多少是个歌手。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Who do you fancy to win the Cup this year? \n 你认为今年谁会赢得杯赛？ \n, [ + (that) ] \n literary \n I fancied (that) I saw something moving in the corner. \n 我觉得看见角落里有东西在动。 \n, ld-fashioned \n This isn t the first time this has happened, I fancy. \n 我想，这不是第一次发生这种事了。 \n, Fancy seeing you here! \n 没想到在这里遇见你！ \n,  They have eight children.   Fancy that (= how surprising)!  \n “他们有8个孩子。”“真想不到啊！” \n, I wanted a simple black dress, nothing fancy. \n 我想要一件简洁的黑色礼服，不要花哨的东西。 \n, The decorations were a little too fancy for my tastes. \n 这种装饰风格过于繁复，不合我的喜好。 \n, fancy cakes \n 花式蛋糕 \n, We stayed in a fancy hotel near the Champs-Élysées. \n 我们住在香榭丽舍大街附近一家豪华的酒店里。 \n, a fancy restaurant \n 豪华餐厅 \n, But for me, parachuting was no passing fancy. \n 但是对我来说，跳伞可不是一时的兴趣。 \n, Laura s taken a fancy to Japanese food. \n 劳拉喜欢上了日本料理。 \n, I looked in a lot of clothes shops but nothing really tickled my fancy. \n 我逛了很多服装店，但没什么衣服让我中意。 \n, She has enough money to buy anything that strikes her fancy. \n 她有足够的钱想买什么就买什么。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfal/ukfalsi025.mp3'),('fare','车费；车票价出租车乘客（餐馆的）饭菜成功；遭遇','uk :feər, us :fer','[Train fares are going up again. \n 火车票又涨价了。 \n, How did you fare in your exams? \n 你考得怎么样？ \n, Low-paid workers will fare badly/well under this government. \n 在这届政府执政期间，低收入工人的境况会很糟／很好。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfag/ukfagge012.mp3'),('financial','财务的；财政的；金融的','uk :faɪˈnæn.ʃəl, us :faɪˈnæn.ʃəl','[financial difficulties/success \n 财政困难／经济上的成功 \n, financial affairs \n 金融事务 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfin/ukfinan003.mp3'),('firm','结实的；坚固的牢固的；稳固的坚决的；坚定的强有力的；紧紧的，牢牢的确定的；坚定不移的严格的，强硬的公司；商号使（土）变硬；使（土）坚实稳定下来；保持不变','uk :fɜːm, us :fɝːm','[I d rather sleep on a firm mattress than a soft one. \n 我宁愿睡硬床垫，也不要软的。 \n, These pears are still too firm to eat. \n 这些梨还太硬，没法吃。 \n, The bridge provided a firm platform for the bungee jumpers. \n 这座桥为蹦极者提供了稳固的平台。 \n, The government remains firm in its opposition to tax reform. \n 政府仍坚决反对税收改革。 \n, a firm handshake \n 强有力的握手 \n, Keep a firm hold of the handrail as you go down. \n 下去时要牢牢抓住扶手。 \n, igurative \n No one seems to have a firm grip on the company at the moment. \n 目前似乎没有人能牢牢掌控公司。 \n, igurative \n You need a firm grasp of mathematics to become an astronaut. \n 要成为宇航员，数学知识必须非常扎实。 \n, He is a firm believer in traditional family values. \n 他坚信应遵循传统的家庭价值观念。 \n, Some people still claim that there is no firm evidence linking smoking with lung cancer. \n 有人仍声称没有确凿的证据表明吸烟与肺癌有关。 \n, I was always very firm with my children - they knew the rules and I made sure they followed them. \n 我对孩子们总是很严格——他们知道规矩，我则监督他们守规矩。 \n, He works for a law firm called Neil and Vigliano. \n 他在一家名为尼尔和维利亚诺的律师事务所供职。 \n, He s just started working for an accountancy firm/a firm of accountants in Cambridge. \n 他刚刚开始在剑桥的一家会计师事务所工作。 \n, Firm the soil around the cuttings and water them in. \n 把插条四周的土压实，再浇上水。 \n, After a turbulent week on the markets, share prices firmed today. \n 经过一周的市场动荡，股票价格今天稳定下来了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfir/ukfirew004.mp3'),('flagpole','旗杆','uk :ˈflæɡ.pəʊl, us :ˈflæɡ.poʊl','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfla/ukflacc009.mp3'),('fling','猛扔，猛投，猛掷迅猛移动；猛地做…气呼呼地说，愤怒地说短暂的欢乐时光','uk :flɪŋ, us :flɪŋ','[He crumpled up the letter and flung it into the fire. \n 他把信揉成一团，猛地扔进火中。 \n,  And you can take your ring back too!  she cried, flinging it down on the table. \n “你可以把你的戒指也拿走！”她喊道，猛地把戒指摔到桌子上。 \n, K informal \n Could you fling the paper over here (= give me the paper)? \n 你能把报纸丢过来吗？ \n, She flung her arms around his neck. \n 她猛地搂住他的脖子。 \n, The door was flung open by the wind. \n 风把门猛地吹开了。 \n, Sergei flung himself down on the sofa. \n 谢尔盖猛地扑倒在沙发上。 \n, K informal \n Let me just fling (= quickly put) a few things into my bag, and I ll be right with you. \n 让我往包里塞几样东西，马上就跟你去。 \n, K informal \n They were flung (= quickly put) in prison. \n 他们很快被投入监狱。 \n, They were flinging bitter accusations at each other. \n 他们彼此破口大骂。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I don t care what you think , she flung (back) at him. \n “我不在乎你怎么想，”她气呼呼地回敬他道。 \n, The girls are going to the beach for one last fling before the end of summer. \n 姑娘们要去海滩享受夏季结束前最后一段短暂的欢乐时光。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfli/ukflick017.mp3'),('flip','（使）快速翻转；迅速翻动翻烤（食物）迅速转售（稍作装修后的房子）以获取利润翻动，翻转（flippant的非正式说法）“不！”（感叹词，表示愠怒）','uk :flɪp, us :flɪp','[I flipped the book (over) to look at the back cover. \n 我很快地把书翻过去看了看封底。 \n, I lost my place in my book when the pages flipped over in the wind. \n 风把书页吹乱了，我找不到正在看的那个地方了。 \n, You turn the machine on by flipping (= operating) the switch on the side. \n 把边上的开关按一下，机器就启动了。 \n, The captains flipped a coin into the air (= made it turn over in the air to see which side it landed on) to decide which side would bat first. \n 两队队长向空中抛出一枚硬币，决定哪一方先击球。 \n, I don t want to spend the rest of my life flipping burgers. \n 我可不想一辈子都翻烤汉堡。 \n, I am going to take three weeks  vacation and flip this house. \n 我要休假三个星期，稍微装修一下这个房子然后卖掉。 \n, a flip of a coin \n 抛硬币 \n, The acrobats were doing somersaults and flips (= jumping and turning their bodies over in the air). \n 杂技演员们正在翻筋斗和空翻。 \n, Oh, flip, I ve missed the bus. \n 哦不！我错过公交车了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfli/ukflick020.mp3'),('flock','>羊群；鸟群；人群>（特定类型的）一群人>（充填垫子等的）软填料；（在墙纸或窗帘上制作凸起图案用的）短绒，绒屑>聚集；蜂拥>用软材料覆盖表面装饰','uk :>flɒk, us :>flɑːk',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,2,0,NULL),('flout','公然藐视，无视，违背（规定、法律或习俗）','uk :flaʊt, us :flaʊt','[Many motorcyclists flout the law by not wearing helmets. \n 许多骑摩托车的人无视法律，不戴头盔。 \n, The orchestra decided to flout convention/tradition, and wear their everyday clothes for the concert. \n 管弦乐队决定一改传统，在音乐会上穿日常服装。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflo/ukflori020.mp3'),('fluent','（指人说某种语言）流利的（语言）讲得流利的','uk :ˈfluː.ənt, us :','[She s fluent in French. \n 她的法语很流利。 \n, He s a fluent Russian speaker. \n 他的俄语讲得很流利。 \n, He speaks fluent Chinese. \n 他汉语讲得很流利。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukfluct004.mp3'),('flustered','心烦意乱的；慌张的；紧张的','uk :ˈflʌs.təd, us :ˈflʌs.tɚd','[She seemed a little flustered. \n 她似乎有点儿紧张。 \n, If I look flustered it s because I m trying to do so many things at once. \n 如果我看上去很慌乱，那是因为我正试图同时做很多件事情。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush003.mp3'),('flutter','（使）飘动，挥动，颤动；拍（翅）；鼓（翼）（心）怦怦乱跳；（胃）颤动一阵兴奋（或激动）（尤指赛马中的）小赌注振动；颤动；忽闪','uk :ˈflʌt.ər, us :ˈflʌt̬.ɚ','[Brightly coloured flags were fluttering in the breeze. \n 鲜艳的彩旗在微风中飘扬。 \n, Leaves fluttered down onto the path. \n 树叶飘落到小径上。 \n, Butterflies fluttered about in the sunshine. \n 蝴蝶在阳光下翩翩飞舞。 \n, A white bird poised on a wire and fluttered its wings. \n 一只白鸟立在电线上，扑打着翅膀。 \n, Every time I think about my exams my stomach flutters! \n 每次一想到考试，我心里就不舒服！ \n, The publication of her first novel last spring caused a flutter of excitement. \n 去年秋天她的第一部小说出版后引起一阵轰动。 \n, Auntie Paula likes to have a bit of a flutter on the horses. \n 葆拉姨妈喜欢在赛马上下一点儿小赌注。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush007.mp3'),('flux','不断的变动，不停的变化（助）熔剂','uk :flʌks, us :flʌks','[Our plans are in a state of flux at the moment. \n 我们的计划目前处在不断变化之中。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukflu/ukflush009.mp3'),('foe','敌人地球之友（一个国际环保组织，Friends of the Earth的缩写）','uk :fəʊ, us :foʊ','[The two countries have united against their common foe. \n 两国联合起来对抗共同的敌人。 \n, They were bitter foes for many years. \n 他们结仇多年。 \n, Foes of the government will be delighting in its current difficulties. \n 政府的敌人会对政府目前的困难处境幸灾乐祸。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfob/ukfob__009.mp3'),('foldaway','可折叠的；折叠式的','uk :ˈfəʊld.ə.weɪ, us :ˈfoʊld.ə.weɪ','[a foldaway bed \n 折叠床 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfob/ukfob__021.mp3'),('formula','惯例；配方；处方公式，方程式分子式（婴儿）配方奶','uk :ˈfɔː.mjə.lə, us :ˈfɔːr.mjə.lə',NULL,'2019-09-25',0,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukforgi030.mp3'),('fortified','（尤指为防御而）加强，增强','uk :ˈfɔː.tɪ.faɪ, us :ˈfɔːr.t̬ə.faɪ','[a fortified town \n 设防的城镇 \n, They hurriedly fortified the village with barricades of carts. \n 他们匆忙用马车搭起路障，加强村子的防御。 \n, The argument had fortified her resolve to prove she was right. \n 这番争论增强了她证明自己正确的决心。 \n, He fortified himself with a drink and a sandwich before driving on. \n 继续开车之前，他喝了杯饮料吃了块三明治来增强体力。 \n, a fruit drink fortified with vitamin C (= with vitamin C added) \n 添加了维生素C的果汁饮料 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukformu028.mp3'),('foundation','>创建；建立>基金会>（幼儿学校）小班>地基；房基>无根据>（化妆打底用的）粉底霜','uk :>faʊnˈdeɪ.ʃ, us :>faʊnˈdeɪ.ʃ',NULL,'2019-09-25',1,1,0,NULL),('fountain','泉水；（尤指具有装饰效果的）喷泉','uk :ˈfaʊn.tɪn, us :ˈfaʊn.tɪn','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfor/ukfortn030.mp3'),('fountain-pen','钢笔','Gāngbǐ','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=fountain-pen&tl=ja&tk=617265.1007429&client=webapp&prev=input'),('foyer','（剧院、宾馆等公共建筑物入口处内的）门厅（房子或公寓的）门廊，前厅','uk :ˈfɔɪ.eɪ, us :ˈfɔɪ.ɚ','[I ll see you downstairs in the foyer in half an hour. \n 我们半个小时以后在楼下门厅见。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfou/ukfours014.mp3'),('fraud','诈骗（罪）骗子；骗人的事物','uk :frɔːd, us :frɑːd','[credit card fraud \n 信用卡诈骗 \n, He is fighting extradition to Hong Kong to face trial on fraud charges. \n 他正在力争免于被引渡到香港就诈骗指控接受审判。 \n, She was a psychic who was later revealed to be a fraud. \n 她是一个通灵巫师，后来被发现是个骗子。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfra/ukfrate006.mp3'),('friction','摩擦力；摩擦（观点不同者之间的）摩擦，不和','uk :ˈfrɪk.ʃən, us :ˈfrɪk.ʃən','[When you rub your hands together the friction produces heat. \n 揉搓双手时，摩擦会产生热量。 \n, There\'s a lot of friction between my wife and my mother. \n 我妻子和我母亲之间有很多龃龉。 \n, Politics is a source of considerable friction in our family. \n 政治问题在我们家是矛盾的一大根源。 \n, Border clashes have led to increased friction between the two countries. \n 边境冲突引发了两国间更大的摩擦。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfri/ukfrica002.mp3'),('frontier','国境，边境（十九世纪时定居者开始搬入并居住的美国西部）前沿地带','uk :ˈfrʌn.tɪər, us :frʌnˈtɪr','[Some of the frontier between Germany and Poland follows the course of the river Oder. \n 德国与波兰的部分边界是沿奥德河划分的。 \n, Nepal has frontiers with both India and China. \n 尼泊尔与中国和印度都接壤。 \n, They lived in a town close to the frontier. \n 他们居住在一个离边界很近的城镇。 \n, The Homestead Act of 1862 gave free land to pioneers who settled the frontier. \n 1862年的《宅地法》免费把土地给予到西部前沿地区定居的先驱者。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukf/ukfro/ukfrom_009.mp3'),('geographic','地理的；地理学的','uk :ˌdʒi.əˈɡræf.ɪ.kəl, us :ˌdʒi.əˈɡræf.ɪ.kəl','[a geographical region \n 地理区域 \n, geographical features \n 地理特征 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgeo/ukgeogr002.mp3'),('gist','要旨，要点；大意','uk :dʒɪst, us :dʒɪst','[That was the gist of what he said. \n 那就是他的话的大意。 \n, I think I got (= understood) the gist of what she was saying. \n 我想我明白她说的话的大意了。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgir/ukgiraf020.mp3'),('glare','（长久的）怒视，瞪眼刺眼的光发出刺眼的光怒视，瞪眼','uk :ɡleər, us :ɡler','[She gave me a fierce glare. \n 她恶狠狠地瞪了我一眼。 \n, Tinted windows will reduce the glare/the sun s glare. \n 有色玻璃窗会遮挡刺眼的阳光。 \n, This screen gives off a lot of glare. \n 这种屏幕发出的光太刺眼。 \n, The sun was glaring right in my eyes. \n 强烈的阳光直刺我的眼睛。 \n, She glared angrily at everyone and stormed out of the room. \n 她横眉怒目地瞪了大家一眼，气呼呼地冲出房间。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglaci027.mp3'),('glimmer','发出微弱的光；隐约闪烁闪烁的微光；微弱的亮光微弱的（好）迹象；一丝，一线','uk :ˈɡlɪm.ər, us :ˈɡlɪm.ɚ','[The lights of the village were glimmering in the distance. \n 远处村庄微弱的灯光时隐时现。 \n, The sky glimmered with stars. \n 天空闪烁着点点星光。 \n, a glimmering candle \n 暗淡摇曳的烛光 \n, We saw a glimmer of light in the distance. \n 我们看到远处有一线微光。 \n, This month s sales figures offer a glimmer of hope for the depressed economy. \n 这个月的销售额给萧条的经济带来一丝希望。 \n, She s never shown a glimmer of interest in classical music. \n 她对古典音乐从没有表现出过一丁点儿兴趣。 \n, The first glimmer of light (= sign of development or understanding) has appeared in the peace talks. \n 和平会谈首次出现了一丝转机。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgla/ukglass026.mp3'),('goggling','（由于惊奇）瞪大眼睛看','uk :ˈɡɒɡ.əl, us :ˈɡɑː.ɡəl','[The cathedral was full of goggling tourists. \n 大教堂里挤满了游客，一个个瞪大眼睛，惊奇地看着。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgod/ukgodpa009.mp3'),('grant','（尤指政府为特殊目的给予个人或组织的）拨款，补助金（通常指官方）同意，准予，授予（常指在表达相反的意见之前表示让步）承认，同意认为…是理所当然的视…为理所当然（而不去表示感激）；（认为理所当然而）不去重视…因为','uk :ɡrɑːnt, us :ɡrænt','[a student/research grant \n 助学金／研究拨款 \n, a local authority/government grant \n 当地行政机构／政府拨款 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n They gave/awarded her a grant to study abroad for one year. \n 他们给／授予她一笔奖学金供她出国留学1年。 \n, [ + two objects ] \n They granted her an entry visa. \n 他们发给她入境签证。 \n, He was granted asylum. \n 他的避难请求被接受了。 \n, ormal \n She granted their request/wish. \n 她答应了他们的请求／满足了他们的愿望。 \n, I grant that it must have been upsetting but even so I think she overreacted. \n 我承认这事肯定很让人心烦，但即使是这样，我觉得她也有点小题大做。 \n, I grant you (= it is true that), it s a difficult situation but I feel sure he could have handled it more sensitively. \n 不错，这种局面是很棘手，但是我确实觉得他本可以更加理智地来处理。 \n, I didn t realize that Melanie hadn t been to college - I suppose I just took it for granted. \n 我不知道梅拉妮没上大学——我只是想当然地认为她上过了。 \n, One of the problems with relationships is that after a while you just take each other for granted. \n 恋爱中会遇到的一个问题是，相处一段时间后，双方就都把对方为自己所做的一切当成理所当然。 \n, Granted (that) the story s true, there s not a lot you can do about it. \n 因为这件事情是真的，你实在没有办法做什么。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgrand029.mp3'),('grapple','（尤指为了得到某物而）扭打，搏斗','uk :ˈɡræp.əl, us :ˈɡræp.əl','[The children grappled for the ball. \n 孩子们为了争球打成一团。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgranu019.mp3'),('greenback','美钞','uk :ˈɡriːn.bæk, us :ˈɡriːn.bæk','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgra/ukgravi026.mp3'),('guilty','>内疚的，愧疚的，自责的>有过失的，犯了罪的，有罪责的>有过错的一方；犯罪的一方','uk :>ˈɡɪl.ti, us :>ˈɡɪl.ti',NULL,'2019-09-25',0,4,0,NULL),('gum','齿龈，牙龈，牙床树胶，树脂胶，粘合剂口香糖（同 chewing gum）；泡泡糖（同 bubble gum）透明果味糖；胶姆糖；橡皮软糖用胶粘','uk :ɡʌm, us :ɡʌm','[sore gums \n 牙龈疼痛 \n, fruit/wine gums \n 水果胶姆糖／酒胶糖 \n, The labels were already gummed to the envelopes. \n 标签已经粘贴在信封上了。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgui/ukguime017.mp3'),('habitually','习惯性地','uk :həˈbɪtʃ.ə.li, us :həˈbɪtʃ.ə.li','[here is something wrong with anyone who is so habitually rude.\n, There were schools where more than half the students were habitually late.\n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukg/ukgyr/ukgyros012.mp3'),('hail','雹，冰雹（同时抛向某人的）一阵招呼，呼喊下冰雹','uk :heɪl, us :heɪl','[a hail of bullets \n 一阵弹雨 \n, The prime minister was greeted with a hail of insults as she arrived at the university. \n 首相来到大学时遭到一阵辱骂。 \n, Shall we hail a taxi? \n 我们要叫出租车吗？ \n, I tried to hail her from across the room. \n 我在屋子的另一端冲她喊。 \n]\n','2019-12-23',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhae/ukhaema015.mp3'),('harass','骚扰；使烦恼，打扰','uk :ˈhær.əs, us :həˈræs','[Stop harassing me! \n 别烦我！ \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhap/ukhapha013.mp3'),('harpsichord','羽管键琴，古键琴','uk :ˈhɑːp.sɪ.kɔːd, us :ˈhɑːrp.sɪ.kɔːrd','[]\n','2019-12-16',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhar/ukharne005.mp3'),('haunting','（因一种令人忧伤的美丽而）让人难忘的，萦绕心头的','uk :ˈhɔːn.tɪŋ, us :ˈhɑːn.t̬ɪŋ','[a haunting melody \n 难忘的旋律 \n, the haunting beauty of Africa \n 非洲令人难忘的美丽 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhas/ukhasty027.mp3'),('hedge','（尤指花园、田块或马路边缘的）树篱保护（或控制、限制）手段让表述内容的严重程度降低的单词（或词组）严格限制避免答复，拐弯抹角，回避','uk :hedʒ, us :hedʒ','[a privet hedge \n 女贞树篱 \n, She\'d made some overseas investments as a hedge against rising inflation in this country. \n 在海外有一些投资，可以抵消该国不断上升的通货膨胀所带来的损失。 \n, We\'ve got permission, but it\'s hedged about/around with strict conditions. \n 我们得到了许可，但却有严格的限制条件。 \n, Stop hedging and tell me what you really think. \n 别再拐弯抹角了，告诉我你的真实想法。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhea/ukheave019.mp3'),('hedge fund','对冲基金','Duìchōng jījīn','\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=hedge fund&tl=ja&tk=889337.763277&client=webapp&prev=input'),('hence','因此，所以从此，从现在起','uk :hens, us :hens','[His mother was Italian, hence his name - Luca. \n 他母亲是意大利人，所以他的名字叫——卢卡。 \n, The project will be completed at the end of the decade, two years hence. \n 本项目将于这个10年期结束时完成，从现在算起还有两年时间。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhel/ukhellu022.mp3'),('hippopotamus','河马','uk :ˌhɪp.əˈpɒt.ə.məs, us :ˌhɪp.əˈpɑː.t̬ə.məs','[]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhim/ukhimal028.mp3'),('hostility','敌意，不友好不同意，不喜欢战斗；战争行为','uk :hɒsˈtɪl.ə.ti, us :hɑːˈstɪl.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2019-10-03',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhor/ukhorsi024.mp3'),('hotspot','多事之地；热点地区；可能发生战争（或骚乱）的地方热闹场所（可接上无线宽带上网的）热点','uk :ˈhɒt.spɒt, us :ˈhɑːt.spɑːt','[The border has become a major hotspot. \n 边境地区已经变成了主要的热点。 \n, The Manhattan is one of the best hotspots in town. \n 曼哈顿是城里最热闹的地方之一。 \n, There are wi-fi hotspots in all our cafés. \n 我们所有的咖啡馆里都有上网热点。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uka/uka33/uka33350.mp3'),('hum','发出连续低沉的声音，嗡嗡作响哼（曲子）忙乱，忙碌；嘈杂持续低沉的噪音；嗡嗡声','uk :hʌm, us :hʌm','[The computers were humming in the background. \n 计算机在背景中嗡嗡作响。 \n, What\'s that strange humming sound? \n 那种奇怪的嗡嗡声是什么？ \n, She hummed to herself as she walked to school. \n 她在上学的路上边走边哼曲子。 \n, I\'ve forgotten how that song goes - could you hum it for me? \n 我忘了那个调子怎么唱了——你能给我哼一下吗？ \n, The bar was really humming last night. \n 昨晚酒吧里一片乱哄哄的。 \n, Our house is on a main road, so we can hear the constant hum of traffic. \n 我们的房子在大路旁，所以能听见持续不断的交通噪声。 \n, There\'s an annoying hum on this computer. \n 这台计算机总是发出一种让人心烦的嗡嗡声。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhuf/ukhuffi018.mp3'),('humdrum','乏味的，单调的，令人厌倦的','uk :ˈhʌm.drʌm, us :ˈhʌm.drʌm','[We lead such a humdrum life/existence. \n 我们的生活／日子过得真是乏味。 \n, Most of the work is fairly humdrum. \n 这工作大部分都相当单调。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman007.mp3'),('humiliation','羞辱','uk :hjuːˌmɪl.iˈeɪ.ʃən, us :hjuːˌmɪl.iˈeɪ.ʃən','[fter the humiliation of last week\'s defeat, the Mets were back on form.\n, Imagine the humiliation of having to apologize.\n, I felt a deep humiliation and wanted the ground to swallow me up.\n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhum/ukhuman017.mp3'),('hunch','直觉；预感弓（背），弯腰','uk :hʌntʃ, us :hʌntʃ','[[ + that ] \n I had a hunch that you d be here. \n 直觉告诉我你会来这儿。 \n, Sometimes you have to be prepared to act on/follow a hunch. \n 有时候你得准备好按直觉行事。 \n, We hunched round the fire to keep warm. \n 我们弓着身子围在火边取暖。 \n, Stand up straight and don t hunch your back. \n 站直了，别弯着腰。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukh/ukhun/ukhunch001.mp3'),('illuminate','为…照明，照亮阐明，解释','uk :ɪˈluː.mɪ.neɪt, us :ɪˈluː.mə.neɪt','[The streets were illuminated with strings of coloured lights. \n 街道被一串串彩灯照亮了。 \n, an article which illuminates the issues at stake \n 对一些紧要的问题进行阐述的文章 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukign/ukignor025.mp3'),('immune','免疫的不受影响的免除的，豁免的','uk :ɪˈmjuːn, us :ɪˈmjuːn',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod011.mp3'),('impact','冲击（力）；撞击（力）（尤指新事物的）巨大影响，强大作用（对…）产生影响','uk :ˈɪm.pækt, us :ˈɪm.pækt','[The impact of the crash reduced the car to a third of its original length. \n 撞车时的冲击力使车身变形，仅剩原长的三分之一。 \n, The bullet explodes on impact (= when it hits another object). \n 子弹击中物体时爆炸。 \n, The anti-smoking campaign had had/made quite an impact on young people. \n 禁烟运动对年轻人影响很大。 \n, The new proposals were intended to soften the impact of the reformed tax system. \n 新的提议旨在减轻改革后的税制所造成的影响。 \n, Falling export rates have impacted (on) the country\'s economy quite considerably. \n 出口率的下降对该国的经济造成了相当大的影响。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimm/ukimmod023.mp3'),('impassable','（道路）不能通行的，无法通过的','uk :ɪmˈpɑː.sə.bəl, us :ɪmˈpæs.ə.bəl','[Many roads were flooded and impassable following the storm. \n 暴风雨过后，许多道路被淹，无法通行。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpar005.mp3'),('implacable','不饶人的；坚定的；无法改变的','uk :ɪmˈplæk.ə.bəl, us :ɪmˈplæk.ə.bəl',NULL,'2019-10-03',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpet012.mp3'),('imply','暗指，暗示正如…所暗示的必然包含；使成为必需','uk :ɪmˈplaɪ, us :ɪmˈplaɪ','[[ + (that) ] \n Are you implying (that) I\'m fat? \n 你是在暗示我长得胖吗？ \n, I\'m not implying anything about your cooking, but could we eat out tonight? \n 我并不是暗示你做的饭不好吃，只是想提议我们今晚去外面吃，好吗？ \n, I detected an implied criticism of the way he was treated. \n 我觉察到他在含蓄地批评自己受到的待遇。 \n, Variable rate loans, as the name implies, have a variable interest rate. \n 可变利率贷款，正如名字所暗示的，是一种利率可能变化的贷款。 \n, Socialism implies equality. \n 社会主义必然包含平等。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimplo002.mp3'),('impressionable','（通常指年轻人）易受影响的','uk :ɪmˈpreʃ.ən.ə.bəl, us :ɪmˈpreʃ.ən.ə.bəl','[He s at that impressionable age when he s very easily led by other children. \n 他正处于那种易受影响的年龄，行为非常容易受其他孩子左右。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukimp/ukimpra012.mp3'),('in force','in large number','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('incandescent','白炽的，白热的极亮的极度愤怒的；极度高兴的杰出的，卓越的','uk :ˌɪn.kænˈdes.ənt, us :ˌɪn.kænˈdes.ənt','[an incandescent lamp \n 白炽灯 \n, The mountain s snow-white peak was incandescent against the blue sky. \n 雪白的山顶在蓝天的映衬下十分耀眼。 \n, He was incandescent with rage. \n 他大发雷霆。 \n, Her beauty had an incandescent quality to it. \n 她貌美绝伦，光彩照人。 \n, an incandescent performance/career \n 炉火纯青的表演／辉煌的事业 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukina/ukinaug015.mp3'),('indice','指数，索引','ˈɪndɪsiːz','null\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'null'),('informally','非公式','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('infrastructure','基础设施','uk :ˈɪn.frəˌstrʌk.tʃər, us :ˈɪn.frəˌstrʌk.tʃɚ','[The war has badly damaged the country\'s infrastructure. \n 战争严重破坏了该国的基础设施。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinf/ukinfor009.mp3'),('inhale','吸气；吸入狼吞虎咽','uk :ɪnˈheɪl, us :ɪnˈheɪl','[She flung open the window and inhaled deeply. \n 她打开窗户，深深地吸了口气。 \n, She became ill shortly after inhaling the fumes. \n 她吸入浓烟后不久就生病了。 \n, Tony inhaled his burger. \n 托尼狼吞虎咽地吃汉堡。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/uking/ukingra011.mp3'),('inlay','镶嵌图案（或装饰）','uk :ˈɪn.leɪ, us :ˈɪn.leɪ','[The walls of the palace are marble with silver inlay. \n 宫殿的墙壁是镶银大理石的。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukini/ukiniti021.mp3'),('insinuate','含沙射影地说，影射','uk :ɪnˈsɪn.ju.eɪt, us :ɪnˈsɪn.ju.eɪt','[[ + (that) ] \n Are you insinuating (that) I m losing my nerve? \n 你是在暗示我胆怯了吗？ \n, What are you insinuating, Daniel? \n 丹尼尔，你究竟在影射什么？ \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsin003.mp3'),('inspection','检查；视察鉴定，查勘（建筑物）','uk :ɪnˈspek.ʃən, us :ɪnˈspek.ʃən','[Her passport seemed legitimate, but on closer inspection, it was found to have been altered. \n 她的护照看似合法，但仔细检查，发现做过手脚。 \n, She arrived to carry out/make a health and safety inspection of the building. \n 她来对大楼进行安全卫生检查。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsin030.mp3'),('institutional','机构的','uk :ˌɪn.stɪˈtʃuː.ʃən.əl, us :ˌɪn.stəˈtuː.ʃən.əl','[The hospital provides typically awful institutional food. \n 医院供应的是公共机构常见的那种难吃的食物。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinspe028.mp3'),('intellectual','智力的，脑力的知识分子，脑力劳动者','uk :ˌɪn.təlˈek.tʃu.əl, us :ˌɪn.t̬əlˈek.tʃu.əl',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsur020.mp3'),('intellectualism','主知主義者','uk :ˌɪn.təlˈek.tʃu.ə.lɪ.zəm, us :ˌɪn.t̬əlˈek.tʃu.ə.lɪ.zəm','[e wasn\'t intimidated by Kerry\'s intellectualism.\n, She encouraged her father to offset his intellectualism with displays of emotion.\n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uki/ukins/ukinsur021.mp3'),('interval','间隔；间距（两点之间的）区间（演出的）幕间休息；（体育比赛的）中间休息，中场休息每隔（一定时间或距离）音程','uk :ˈɪn.tə.vəl, us :ˈɪn.t̬ɚ.vəl','[We see each other at regular intervals - usually about once a month. \n 我们定期见面——通常大约是每月一次。 \n, The plants should be spaced at six-inch intervals. \n 这些植物应该以六英尺的间隔栽种。 \n, There will be two 20-minute intervals during the opera. \n 歌剧演出中有两次20分钟的幕间休息。 \n, He scored his first goal of the match three minutes after the interval. \n 下半场刚开始3分钟，他就射入了他本场比赛的第一个进球。 \n, In the event of fire, the alarm will sound at 15-second intervals/at intervals of 15 seconds. \n 发生火灾时，警报每隔15秒就会响一次。 \n, an interval of a fifth (= between one note and another one four notes higher) \n 五度音程 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukinter318.mp3'),('intonation','（尤指对话语意义有影响的）语调，声调（演奏或歌唱时音符的）音准','uk :ˌɪn.təˈneɪ.ʃən, us :ˌɪn.təˈneɪ.ʃən','[The end of a sentence that is not a question is usually marked by falling intonation. \n 非疑问句的句尾通常用降调。 \n, The violinist had good intonation, and a wonderful pure tone. \n 这位小提琴演奏家对音准把握得很好，音色也很纯。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintes019.mp3'),('intoxicating','（饮品）醉人的（经历或想法）令人陶醉的，令人极其兴奋的','uk :ɪnˈtɒk.sɪ.keɪ.tɪŋ, us :ɪnˈtɑːk.sɪ.keɪ.t̬ɪŋ','[intoxicating liquor \n 烈酒 \n, an intoxicating thought \n 令人陶醉的想法 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintes024.mp3'),('intrusive','打搅的；侵扰的','uk :ɪnˈtruː.sɪv, us :ɪnˈtruː.sɪv','[intrusive questioning \n 唐突的盘问 \n, intrusive lighting \n 扰人的照明 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukint/ukintru004.mp3'),('invest','投（资），投入','uk :ɪnˈvest, us :ɪnˈvest','[The institute will invest five million in the project. \n 该机构将在这个项目上投资500万。 \n, He\'s not certain whether to invest in the property market. \n 他拿不定主意该不该投资房地产市场。 \n, You have all invested significant amounts of time and energy in making this project the success that it is. \n 你们都为这个项目的成功投入了大量的时间和精力。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinv/ukinvei015.mp3'),('investigator','调查人员','uk :ɪnˈves.tɪ.ɡeɪ.tər, us :ɪnˈves.tə.ɡeɪ.t̬ɚ','[Investigators have studied the possible effects of contamination. \n 调查人员研究了污染可能造成的后果。 \n, a private investigator \n 私家侦探 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukinv/ukinvei019.mp3'),('irony','具有讽刺意味的是','uk :ˈaɪ.rə.ni, us :ˈaɪ.rə.ni','null\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'null'),('isolate','隔离；孤立；分离隔离（人或动物）孤立（人、国家或组织）','uk :ˈaɪ.sə.leɪt, us :ˈaɪ.sə.leɪt','[A high wall isolated the house from the rest of the village. \n 一堵高墙将这栋房子与村庄的其他部分隔离开来。 \n, They tried to isolate (= find) the cause of the problem. \n 他们试图找出问题的原因。 \n, pecialized \n Virus particles were eventually isolated from the tissue. \n 终于将病毒粒子与组织分离开了。 \n, He was isolated from all the other prisoners. \n 他被与其他所有囚犯隔离开来。 \n, This policy will isolate minority groups and prevent integration. \n 这一政策将孤立少数人群社区，阻碍融合。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uki/ukiso/ukisola001.mp3'),('jeopardise','使处于危险境地；危及，损害','uk :ˈdʒep.ə.daɪz, us :ˈdʒep.ɚ.daɪz','[She knew that by failing her finals she could jeopardize her whole future. \n 她知道考试不及格会影响自己的整个前程。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjeh/ukjehov010.mp3'),('jewish','犹太教','ˈdʒuː.ɪʃ',NULL,'2019-09-25',0,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjet/ukjetsa012.mp3'),('judiciary','（政府的）司法部；司法系统','uk :dʒuːˈdɪʃ.ər.i, us :dʒuːˈdɪʃ.ɚ.i',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjud/ukjudic003.mp3'),('jurisdiction','司法权；管辖权；审判权','uk :ˌdʒʊə.rɪsˈdɪk.ʃən, us :ˌdʒʊr.ɪsˈdɪk.ʃən','[The court has no jurisdiction in/over cases of this kind. \n 该法庭无权审判此类案件。 \n, School admissions are not under/within our jurisdiction. \n 我们无权批准入学。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjun/ukjun__015.mp3'),('justification','正当的理由；辩解','uk :ˌdʒʌs.tɪ.fɪˈkeɪ.ʃən, us :ˌdʒʌs.tə.fəˈkeɪ.ʃən',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukj/ukjun/ukjun__023.mp3'),('keen','热衷的；热心的；渴望的强烈的，激烈的敏锐的；敏捷的尖利的；寒风刺骨的（尤指因某人死去而）恸哭热衷；渴望','uk :kiːn, us :kiːn',NULL,'2019-09-25',1,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukk/ukkaz/ukkazak010.mp3'),('lane','乡间小路；小巷，小街，胡同车道；（田径比赛的）跑道；泳道航道，航线','uk :leɪn, us :leɪn','[He drives so fast along those narrow country lanes. \n 在那些狭窄的乡间小路上他把车开得飞快。 \n, I live at the end of Church Lane. \n 我住在教堂巷的最里面。 \n, a bus/bike/cycle lane \n 公共汽车／自行车车道 \n, The northbound lane is closed because of an accident. \n 北行的车道因发生事故已经封闭。 \n, I find driving in the fast lane very stressful. \n 我发现在快车道行驶时精神非常紧张。 \n, The German runners/swimmers are in lanes 4 and 6. \n 德国径赛／游泳选手处在第4道和第6道。 \n, The English Channel is the busiest shipping lane in the world. \n 英吉利海峡是世界上最繁忙的水运航道。 \n]\n','2019-12-16',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklai/uklaidb003.mp3'),('lapis-lazuli','青金石','/ˈlæpɪs ˈlæzjʊli','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=lapis-lazuli&tl=ja&tk=439866.33358&client=webapp&prev=input'),('leaflet','传单，活页；（单页）广告散发，发放（传单或广告）','uk :ˈliː.flət, us :ˈliː.flət','[Demonstrators handed out leaflets to passers-by. \n 示威者向路人发放传单。 \n, A leaflet about the new bus services came through the door today. \n 今天从门缝塞进来一张介绍公交车新增服务的广告。 \n, They leafleted the area two weeks before the event. \n 活动开始前两周他们就在该地区散发了广告。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv013.mp3'),('lecture','（尤指面向学生的）讲座，课教训，训斥，斥责（常指在大学里）讲课，讲授教训，训斥，斥责','uk :ˈlek.tʃər, us :ˈlek.tʃɚ','[We went to a lecture on Italian art. \n 我们去参加了一个关于意大利艺术的讲座。 \n, Who s giving the lecture this afternoon? \n 今天下午的课由谁来讲？ \n, My dad gave me a lecture on the evils of alcohol last night. \n 昨天晚上爸爸教训了我一顿，给我讲了酒的危害。 \n, For ten years she lectured in law. \n 她教了10年的法律课。 \n, She travelled widely in North America, lecturing on women s rights. \n 她到北美各地宣讲妇女的权利。 \n, His parents used to lecture him on his table manners. \n 以前他的父母经常批评他的餐桌礼仪。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklea/uklearn027.mp3'),('leech','水蛭，蚂蟥（指人）吸血鬼，寄生虫','uk :liːtʃ, us :liːtʃ','[]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukldr/ukldriv002.mp3'),('legislate','立法','uk :ˈledʒ.ɪ.sleɪt, us :ˈledʒ.ə.sleɪt','[They promised to legislate against cigarette advertising. \n 他们承诺要立法来打击香烟广告。 \n, It\'s hard to legislate for (= make a law that will protect) the ownership of an idea. \n 通过立法来保护创意所有权非常困难。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/ukleg/uklegal012.mp3'),('legisl