igarette&tl=ja&tk=587545.967533&client=webapp&prev=input'),('loophole','（协议或法律的）漏洞，空子，破绽','uk :ˈluːp.həʊl, us :ˈluːp.hoʊl','[tax loopholes \n 税法的漏洞 \n, The company employed lawyers to find loopholes in environmental protection laws. \n 该公司雇用律师来寻找环境保护法的漏洞。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklon/uklonel026.mp3'),('loose','松的，松动的（头发）松散的，披着的，散开的松散的，散开的（衣服）宽松的，肥大的未严加控制的；不严谨的，不精确的不道德的；淫荡的敞开了说，放开了说，自由表达','uk :luːs, us :luːs','[There were some loose wires hanging out of the wall. \n 墙上搭着几根没有接好的电线。 \n, The nails in the wall had worked themselves loose. \n 桥上的钉子已经松动了。 \n, The prisoners were so thin that their skin hung loose. \n 囚犯们瘦得很厉害，身上的皮肤都松垮垮地垂着。 \n, Her hair was hanging loose to her shoulders. \n 她的头发松松地垂在肩上。 \n, A few loose sheets of paper were lying around. \n 几张纸散落在地板上。 \n, Wear comfortable, loose clothing to your exercise class. \n 上体育课的时候要穿些舒适宽松的衣服。 \n, It s a fairly loose adaptation of the novel. \n 它是根据小说的大致内容改编而成的。 \n, It s only a loose translation of the poem. \n 这只是那首诗的不准确的译文。 \n, a loose woman \n 荡妇 \n, The coach loosed an angry tirade against his team. \n 教练滔滔不绝地怒斥自己的球队。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklon/uklonel029.mp3'),('lycanthropy','狼人','lī-ˈkan-thrə-pē','null\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'null'),('lyrics','（尤指流行歌曲的）歌词抒情诗（尤指诗歌和歌曲）抒情的','uk :ˈlɪr.ɪk, us :ˈlɪr.ɪk','[Paul Simon writes the lyrics for most of his songs. \n 保罗‧西蒙的歌大多都是他自己写的词。 \n, William Wordsworth wrote lyric poetry/was a lyric poet. \n 威廉‧华兹华斯创作抒情诗／是一位抒情诗人。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukl/uklyc/uklycee013.mp3'),('mahogany','（做家具的）红木，桃花心木','uk :məˈhɒɡ.ən.i, us :məˈhɑː.ɡən.i','[a handsome mahogany desk \n 美观大方的红木书桌 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukm/ukmag/ukmagni013.mp3'),('mansion','大厦；大楼；豪宅','