, us :ˈniːt.li','[His clothes are all neatly folded in their drawers. \n 他的衣服都整齐地叠放在他们的抽屉里。 \n, The announcement was neatly timed to coincide with the release of their new album. \n 这项消息很巧妙地安排在他们的新专辑推出的时候公布。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknav/uknaval029.mp3'),('negotiation','谈判，磋商，洽谈','uk :nəˌɡəʊ.ʃiˈeɪ.ʃən, us :nəˌɡoʊ.ʃiˈeɪ.ʃən','[The agreement was reached after a series of difficult negotiations. \n 该协议是在经历了一系列艰难的谈判之后达成的。 \n, The exact details of the agreement are still under negotiation. \n 协议的确切条款尚待磋商。 \n, Negotiation for the pay increase is likely to take several weeks. \n 加薪谈判可能要持续数周。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneg/uknegot003.mp3'),('neon','氖，氖气','uk :ˈniː.ɒn, us :ˈniː.ɑːn','[a neon light/sign \n 霓虹灯／霓虹灯广告牌 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/ukneg/uknegot023.mp3'),('nickel','镍（美国或加拿大的）5分镍币','uk :ˈnɪk.əl, us :ˈnɪk.əl','[a nickel alloy \n 镍合金 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknic/ukniche003.mp3'),('nonconformity','不合规','uk :ˌnɒn.kənˈfɔː.mə.ti, us :ˌnɑːn.kənˈfɔːr.mə.t̬i',NULL,'2019-10-03',2,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknon/uknonag011.mp3'),('notable','显要的；显著的；值得注意的显要人物；名流','uk :ˈnəʊ.tə.bəl, us :ˈnoʊ.t̬ə.bəl','[a notable collection of rare plants \n 一批引人注目的奇花异草 \n, Getting both sides to agree was a notable achievement. \n 使双方达成共识是一项显著的成就。 \n, This attractive building is particularly notable for its woodland setting. \n 这幢漂亮的建筑因其树林背景而格外引人注目。 \n, Other notables among his pupils were the kings of Saudi Arabia and Thailand. \n 他的学生中，另外两位显要人物是沙特阿拉伯国王和泰国国王。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukn/uknos/uknosh_011.mp3'),('notion','观念；看法缝纫用品；缝纫用品店；缝纫