mplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce024.mp3'),('obstacle','障碍；阻碍；妨碍','uk :ˈɒb.stə.kəl, us :ˈɑːb.stə.kəl','[The biggest obstacle in our way was a tree trunk in the road. \n 我们路上最大的障碍是横在路上的一棵树。 \n, This decision has removed the last obstacle to the hostages\' release. \n 这个决定清除了释放人质的最后障碍。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsce025.mp3'),('obstruct','阻塞，堵塞，阻挡（道路、通道、入口等）阻碍；阻止，阻挠；妨碍','uk :əbˈstrʌkt, us :əbˈstrʌkt',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsti004.mp3'),('occasional','偶尔的；不经常的','uk :əˈkeɪ.ʒən.əl, us :əˈkeɪ.ʒən.əl','[I play the occasional game of tennis. \n 我偶尔打打网球。 \n, He has the occasional cigar after dinner. \n 他饭后偶尔抽支雪茄。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukobs/ukobsti023.mp3'),('offset','补偿；抵消；弥补支付具有减排作用的东西，以弥补之前的排放所造成的损害','uk :ˌɒfˈset, us :ˌɑːfˈset','[The extra cost of travelling to work is offset by the lower price of houses here. \n 这里低廉的房价抵消了因上班路途远而产生的额外费用。 \n, K \n He keeps his petrol receipts because petrol is one of the expenses that he can offset against tax (= can show to the government as being a business cost, and so not pay tax). \n 他保留着他的汽油费收据，因为汽油费是可以抵扣税款的一项开支。 \n, We offset all our long-haul flights. \n 我们补偿了之前长途运输机的排放所带来的损害。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukoff/ukoffen024.mp3'),('opinion','>意见，看法，主张>（一群人的）意见，看法；民意>看法，评价>专家意见；鉴定','uk :>əˈpɪn.jən, us :>əˈpɪn.jən',NULL,'2019-09-25',0,3,0,NULL),('ornament','装饰物，饰品装饰，摆设装饰，点缀','uk :ˈɔː.nə.mənt, us :ˈɔːr.nə.mənt','[a glass ornament \n 玻璃饰物 \n, garden ornaments such as statues and fountains \n 如雕像、喷泉等花园装饰物 \n, The building relies on clever design rather than on ornament for its impressive effect. \n 这幢大楼依靠其巧妙设计而非装饰给人留下了深刻的印象。 \n, She ornamented her letters with little drawings in the margin. \n 她在信的页边空白处画上小图案来作装饰。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uko/ukori/ukorigi005.mp3'),('out-in-force','in','null','null\n','2019-10-09',0,1,0,'null'),('outpost','前哨','Qiánshào','\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=outpost &tl=ja&tk=945297.547045&client=webapp&prev=input'),('pale','（脸色或肤色）苍白的，白的暗淡的；浅的，淡的变苍白，失去血色','uk :peɪl, us :peɪl','[You re looking pale - are you feeling well? \n 你看上去脸色苍白——你病了吗？ \n, She has a naturally pale complexion and dark hair. \n 她天生肤色白皙，头发乌黑。 \n, She wore a pale blue hat. \n 她戴着一顶浅蓝色的帽子。 \n, pale winter sunlight \n 冬天惨淡的日光 \n, His face paled and he looked as if he might faint. \n 他脸色变得苍白，看上去像要晕倒一样。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpad/ukpaddl025.mp3'),('palm','手掌，手心给（某人）看手相（算命）棕榈树（变戏法或偷窃时）把…藏在手心内','uk :pɑːm, us :pɑːm','[This tiny device fits into the palm of your hand. \n 这种微型装置可以放入你的掌心。 \n, date palms \n 枣椰树 \n, palm fronds \n 棕榈叶 \n, The island has long golden beaches fringed by palm trees. \n 这个小岛周围金色海滩绵延，环抱于绿色的棕榈中。 \n, I suspected that he had palmed a playing card. \n 我怀疑他把一张纸牌藏在了手心里。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpal/ukpalef019.mp3'),('panel','（选定的）专家小组嵌板，镶板仪表板；操纵台嵌板，镶板','uk :ˈpæn.əl, us :ˈpæn.əl','[The competition will be judged by a panel of experts. \n 这次竞赛将由一个专家小组来评判。 \n, a beautiful old door with oak panels \n 一扇嵌有橡木板的漂亮的老式门 \n, White silk panels were inset into the sides of the dress. \n 衣边镶有白绸布。 \n, At the bottom of each page is a panel with grammatical information. \n 每页底部都有语法知识板块。 \n, a control/instrument panel \n 控制／仪表板 \n, The walls of the dining hall were panelled in oak. \n 餐厅的墙上嵌了橡木板。 \n, a panelled room/wall/door \n 有镶板的房间／墙／门 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpam/ukpampe018.mp3'),('parlor','（提供某种服务或销售某种商品的）店堂，店铺（尤指旧时的）起居室，客厅，会客室','uk :ˈpɑː.lər, us :ˈpɑːr.lɚ','[a beauty parlour \n 美容院 \n, an ice-cream/pizza parlour \n 冷饮店／比萨屋 \n, the front parlour \n 前厅 \n, an Edwardian parlour \n 爱德华七世时代的客厅 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparis016.mp3'),('parlour','（提供某种服务或销售某种商品的）店堂，店铺（尤指旧时的）起居室，客厅，会客室','uk :ˈpɑː.lər, us :ˈpɑːr.lɚ','[a beauty parlour \n 美容院 \n, an ice-cream/pizza parlour \n 冷饮店／比萨屋 \n, the front parlour \n 前厅 \n, an Edwardian parlour \n 爱德华七世时代的客厅 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparis016.mp3'),('particularly','特别，尤其，异乎寻常地','uk :pəˈtɪk.jə.lə.li, us :pɚˈtɪk.jə.lɚ.li','[We\'re particularly interested to hear from people who speak two or more European languages. \n 我们特别希望能收到说两种或两种以上欧洲语言的人的来信。 \n, I didn\'t particularly want to go, but I had to. \n 我并不是特别想去，但我不得不去。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpar/ukparsi026.mp3'),('patriot','爱国者','uk :ˈpæt.ri.ət, us :ˈpeɪ.tri.ɑːt',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpat/ukpatie016.mp3'),('pension','养老金；退休金；抚恤金','uk :ˈpen.ʃən, us :ˈpen.ʃən','[S \n a government pension \n 政府养老金 \n, K \n a state pension. \n 政府养老金 \n, He won\'t be able to draw (= receive) his pension until he\'s 65. \n 他得等到65岁以后才能领取养老金。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpen/ukpenet022.mp3'),('peril','巨大的危险；险情，险境自冒风险做…','uk :ˈper.əl, us :ˈper.əl','[I never felt that my life was in peril. \n 我从未意识到我的生命受到了严重的威胁。 \n, The journey through the mountains was fraught with peril (= full of dangers). \n 穿越山岭的旅途充满了危险。 \n, Teenagers must be warned about the perils of unsafe sex. \n 必须告诫青少年不安全性行为存在重大危险。 \n, We underestimate the destructiveness of war at our peril. \n 我们低估了战争的破坏性，这对我们是很危险的。 \n]\n','2019-09-27',1,5,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperfu006.mp3'),('perpetual','永久的，永恒的；长期的不断重复的；永无休止的','uk :pəˈpetʃ.u.əl, us :pɚˈpetʃ.u.əl','[They lived in perpetual fear of being discovered. \n 他们长期生活在恐惧中，担心被发现。 \n, He has hard, cold eyes and his mouth is set in a perpetual sneer. \n 他双眼又凶又冷，嘴角总是挂着一丝蔑笑。 \n, a perpetual student \n 终生学习者 \n, perpetual vandalism \n 对公共财物不断的蓄意破坏 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperki029.mp3'),('pervert','侵害；歪曲；使走上邪路，使变坏妨碍司法公正，枉法性行为反常者，性变态者','uk :pəˈvɜːt, us :pɚˈvɝːt','[Her ideas have been shamelessly perverted to serve the president s propaganda campaign. \n 为了配合总统的宣传活动，她的想法被无耻地曲解了。 \n, The history teacher tried to pervert (= persuade into unacceptable sexual activity) the boys by showing them pornographic magazines. \n 这名历史教师给男学生们看色情杂志，想引他们走上邪路。 \n, The two police officers were charged with perverting the course of justice by fabricating evidence in the trial. \n 两名警官因在审判中伪造证据被控妨碍司法公正。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukper/ukperv_011.mp3'),('petition','请愿书（向法院递交的）上诉书，诉状（向法院）递交上诉书，上诉','uk :pəˈtɪʃ.ən, us :pəˈtɪʃ.ən','[I signed a petition against the proposed closure of the local hospital today. \n 今天我在反对关闭当地医院的请愿书上签了名。 \n, She s filing a petition for divorce. \n 她将要递交离婚诉状。 \n, They re petitioning for/about better facilities for disabled people. \n 他们正在请愿，希望当局能为残疾人安装更好的设施。 \n, [ + obj + to infinitive ] \n I think we should petition the government to increase the grant for the project. \n 我认为我们应该请求政府增加对该项目的拨款。 \n, She is petitioning for a re-trial. \n 她将上诉要求重审。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpet/ukpeter006.mp3'),('phase-out','停用','null','null\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'null'),('phony','虚伪的；假冒的，伪造的','uk :ˈfəʊ.ni, us :ˈfoʊ.ni','[All salespeople seem to have the same phoney smile. \n 所有推销员的微笑似乎都一样，假惺惺的。 \n, He gave the police a phoney address. \n 他给了警察一个假地址。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphone004.mp3'),('phrase','短语说法；用语；警句乐句；乐节用…方式表达，以…措词表达','uk :freɪz, us :freɪz','[We are governed, in Lord Hailsham s famous phrase, by an  elective dictatorship . \n 套用一下黑尔什姆勋爵的名言，我们被“选举出来的独裁者”统治着。 \n, The declaration was carefully/cleverly/tactfully, etc. phrased. \n 宣言措词谨慎／巧妙／圆滑等。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphoto010.mp3'),('physicist','物理学家','uk :ˈfɪz.ɪ.sɪst, us :ˈfɪz.ɪ.sɪst',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpho/ukphoto018.mp3'),('pickle','腌菜，泡菜；菜酱醋渍黄瓜（片）；腌黄瓜（片）（用醋或盐水）腌制，腌渍','uk :ˈpɪk.əl, us :ˈpɪk.əl','[cheese and pickle sandwiches \n 奶酪和腌菜三明治 \n, Have some pickles with your sandwich. \n 在色拉里加些泡菜。 \n, a sweet/sour pickle \n 甜／酸黄瓜 \n, The onions had been pickled in brine. \n 洋葱已经在卤水中腌过了。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpia/ukpiano016.mp3'),('pillow','枕头坐垫；靠垫（同 cushion）','uk :ˈpɪl.əʊ, us :ˈpɪl.oʊ','[Do you prefer a feather pillow or a foam pillow? \n 你喜欢羽绒枕头还是海绵枕头？ \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpig/ukpigmy028.mp3'),('pipe','管；管子；管道烟斗笛（子）；管乐器（bagpipes 的另一种说法）（管风琴的）音管计算机键盘上的“|”键用尖嗓子说；尖声唱管道运输','uk :paɪp, us :paɪp','[a water/gas/sewer pipe \n 供水／煤气／下水管道 \n, a burst/fractured/leaking pipe \n 爆裂／破裂／泄漏的管道 \n, I ordered some tea for myself and lit my pipe. \n 我叫了茶，点着了烟斗。 \n, Hot water is piped to all apartments from the central boiler room. \n 热水从中央锅炉房通过管道输送到每个公寓套房。 \n, igurative \n Music is piped throughout the hotel complex. \n 音乐声在整座酒店大楼里回荡。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpin/ukpinkn023.mp3'),('pledge','誓言；诺言；保证发誓；保证','uk :pledʒ, us :pledʒ','[[ + to infinitive ] \n All the candidates have given/made pledges not to raise taxes if they are elected. \n 所有的候选人都保证当选后不增税。 \n, Thousands of people made pledges (= promised to give money) to the charity campaign. \n 数千人许诺向救助儿童慈善运动捐款。 \n, I give you this ring as a pledge of my everlasting love for you. \n 我把这枚戒指送给你作为我永远爱你的信物。 \n, We are asking people to pledge their support for our campaign. \n 我们正请求人们承诺支持我们的运动。 \n, If you join the armed forces, you have to pledge allegiance to your country. \n 如果参军，你必须宣誓效忠你的祖国。 \n, So far, £50,000 has been pledged (= people have promised to pay this amount) in response to the appeal. \n 到目前为止，人们已承诺捐款5万英镑以响应这项呼吁。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n Both sides have pledged to end the fighting. \n 双方均已保证停战。 \n, I\'ve been pledged to secrecy. \n 我已发誓保守秘密。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukple/ukplebb008.mp3'),('poignancy','激痛','uk :ˈpɔɪ.njən.si, us :ˈpɔɪ.njən.si','[he production took on added poignancy due to the director\'s recent death.\n, The poem has a haunting poignancy.\n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpog/ukpogos003.mp3'),('pop-out','弹出','Dànchū','\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=pop-out&tl=ja&tk=443174.63314&client=webapp&prev=input'),('popinjay','自负的家伙','uk :ˈpɒp.ɪn.dʒeɪ, us :ˈpɑː.pɪn.dʒeɪ','[e regarded his rival as a conceited popinjay.\n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/c/cdo/cdo03/cdo0318ukpopi1094.mp3'),('populist','平民主义的；民粹主义的','uk :ˈpɒp.jə.lɪst, us :ˈpɑː.pjə.lɪst','[a populist manifesto \n 民粹主义宣言 \n, a populist leader \n 民粹主义领袖 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpop/ukpopsi013.mp3'),('portfolios','公文包；文件夹（尤指艺术家的）代表作选辑（个人或机构的）投资组合（部长或大臣）职务；（部长或大臣）职责不管部的（指在英国政府中任要职但并不具体负责某个部门）','uk :ˌpɔːtˈfəʊ.li.əʊ, us :ˌpɔːrtˈfoʊ.li.oʊ','[She\'s trying to build up a portfolio of work to show during job interviews. \n 她正想整理出自己的代表作以便找工作面试时展示一下。 \n, The prime minister offered her the foreign affairs portfolio. \n 首相邀请她出任外交部长。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta013.mp3'),('portrait','肖像，画像；人像照片电影（或书中）的描写，描述；表现竖向（描述计算机文件打印的一种方式，即纸的短边置于顶部和底部）','uk :ˈpɔː.trət, us :ˈpɔːr.trɪt','[She s commissioned an artist to paint her portrait/paint a portrait of her. \n 她委托一位画家为她画一幅肖像。 \n, a portrait gallery \n 肖像画廊 \n, a portrait painter \n 肖像画家 \n, Her latest novel paints a very vivid portrait of the aristocracy in the 1920s. \n 她最新的一部小说生动地描绘了20世纪20年代的贵族生活。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta025.mp3'),('portray','描绘，描述，描写把（某人）刻画成，将（某人）塑造成','uk :pɔːˈtreɪ, us :pɔːrˈtreɪ',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpor/ukporta027.mp3'),('pouch','小袋；一小袋东西（某些雌性动物的）育儿袋（某些动物贮存食物的）喉囊，颊袋','uk :paʊtʃ, us :paʊtʃ','[All our electric shavers are supplied with a free travel pouch. \n 我们的电动剃须刀都免费提供一个旅行套。 \n, Food sealed in foil pouches lasts for a long time. \n 密封在箔纸袋中的食物可以放很长时间。 \n, Kangaroos carry their young in pouches. \n 袋鼠将它们的幼崽放在育儿袋中。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpot/ukpotti003.mp3'),('precious','珍贵的，宝贵的过分讲究的，做作的（表示讨厌和／或恼怒）宝贝似的极其，非常（同 very）','uk :ˈpreʃ.əs, us :ˈpreʃ.əs','[a precious gift \n 珍贵的礼物 \n, a precious moment/memory \n 宝贵的时刻／记忆 \n, Clean water is a precious commodity in many parts of the world. \n 在世界上很多地方洁净的水是昂贵的商品。 \n, You re so precious to me. \n 你对我来说就是珍宝。 \n, He s so precious about his work that he never gets anything done. \n 他对自己的活儿太讲究了，反而什么都做不成。 \n, Don t you hate the precious way she speaks, pronouncing each single consonant so precisely. \n 她讲话做作的样子真让人讨厌，每个辅音都发得那么准确。 \n, You and your precious car - it s all you re interested in! \n 你心里只有你和你那辆宝贝车！ \n, Lots of people will start, but precious few will finish. \n 许多人将开始去做，但极少数能完成。 \n, Be careful - you ll be precious little help if you come back injured. \n 小心——如果你受了伤回来就帮不上什么忙了。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpra/ukpraye022.mp3'),('premium','奖金，津贴；加价；附加费保险费优质汽油，高级汽油（品质）高级的；优质的，顶级的','uk :ˈpriː.mi.əm, us :','[We re willing to pay a premium for the best location. \n 为了得到最好的地段，我们愿意多支付些钱。 \n, Because of their location, these offices attract a premium. \n 由于地段好，这些办公室租金更高。 \n, The modified cars are available at a premium of five percent over the original price. \n 改进后的汽车的售价要比原价高5%。 \n, The busy shopper puts a premium on (= appreciates and will pay more for) finding everything in one big store. \n 时间有限的购物者若能在一家大商店买齐所有的东西，价钱高点儿也是愿意的。 \n, Car insurance premiums have increased this year. \n 今年汽车保险费涨了。 \n, The premiums for healthcare plans are high. \n 保健计划的保险费很高。 \n, premium ice cream \n 优质冰激凌 \n, The building is on a premium site. \n 这幢大楼建在一块风水宝地上。 \n]\n','2019-12-10',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukpremi005.mp3'),('prerogative','独有的权利（或权力），特权','uk :prɪˈrɒɡ.ə.tɪv, us :prɪˈrɑː.ɡə.t̬ɪv',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpre/ukprepo008.mp3'),('primeval','原始的；早期的','uk :praɪˈmiː.vəl, us :praɪˈmiː.vəl','[primeval forests \n 原始森林 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpri/ukprice029.mp3'),('profile','传略；人物简介公众注意（面部的）侧面（像）','uk :ˈprəʊ.faɪl, us :ˈproʊ.faɪl','[We need to increase our company s profile in Asia. \n 我们需要扩大公司在亚洲的影响力。 \n, There is a growing number of women in high-profile positions (= positions which they are noticed) in the government. \n 在备受注目的政府职位上，女性的数量在逐渐增长。 \n, Drawing profiles is somehow easier than drawing the full face. \n 不知为什么画侧面像要比画整张脸容易。 \n, a strong profile \n 轮廓分明的侧影 \n, The actor is photographed in profile, smoking a cigarette. \n 这个演员被人从侧面拍了一张抽烟的照片。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi002.mp3'),('profound','强烈的；深沉的；极度的造诣深的；思想深邃的','uk :prəˈfaʊnd, us :prəˈfaʊnd',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprofi013.mp3'),('progressive','逐渐的；渐进的（指思想或体制）进步的，先进的累进（税）的（动词）进行时的支持进步政策者；改革派人士','uk :prəˈɡres.ɪv, us :prəˈɡres.ɪv','[There s been a progressive decline in the standard of living over the past few years. \n 最近几年的生活水平每况愈下。 \n, a progressive disease \n 慢性病 \n, progressive ideas/attitudes \n 进步的思想／态度 \n, The left of the party is pressing for a more progressive social policy. \n 该政党的左派敦促实行更加进步的社会政策。 \n, a progressive school \n 实行进步教育法的学校 \n,  He s working hard at the moment  is an example of the present progressive form of the verb  work . \n He s working hard at the moment 是动词 work 的现在进行时的一个例子。 \n,  I was eating when the phone rang  is an example of the past progressive. \n I was eating when the phone rang 是过去进行时的一个例子。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr002.mp3'),('projectile','投掷物；抛射物；发射物（尤指子弹、炮弹等）投射的，推进的','uk :prəˈdʒek.taɪl, us :prəˈdʒek.təl','[The second projectile exploded after hitting a tank. \n 第二发炮弹击中坦克后爆炸了。 \n, projectile weapons \n 投射武器 \n, projectile vomiting \n 喷射性呕吐 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprogr011.mp3'),('prone','易于遭受（疾病）的；有（消极）倾向的俯卧的，趴着的较常碰到…问题的','uk :prəʊn, us :proʊn','[I ve always been prone to headaches. \n 我总是容易头疼。 \n, He was prone to depression even as a teenager. \n 甚至在青少年时期他就容易情绪抑郁。 \n, She s prone to exaggerate, that s for sure. \n 她喜欢夸大其词，这一点是肯定的。 \n, The photograph showed a man lying prone on the pavement, a puddle of blood around his head. \n 这张照片上一名男子趴在人行道上，头部周围有一滩血。 \n, accident-prone \n 易出事故的 \n, injury-prone \n 易受伤的 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpromi022.mp3'),('proposal','建议；计划；提案求婚','uk :prəˈpəʊ.zəl, us :prəˈpoʊ.zəl','[Congress has rejected the latest economic proposal put forward by the President. \n 议会否决了总统最近提出的经济计划。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n There has been an angry reaction to the government\'s proposal to reduce unemployment benefit. \n 政府削减失业救济金的计划遭到了强烈的反对。 \n, Have you read Steve\'s proposals for the new project? \n 你看了史蒂夫对新项目的建议了吗？ \n, [ + that ] \n There was anger at the proposal that a UN peacekeeping force should be sent to the area. \n 有人对向该地区派遣联合国维和部队的建议很恼火。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo007.mp3'),('propose','建议；提议；提出提名，推荐（某人）担任某职（或参加某组织）求婚提议为…祝酒；提议为…干杯计划，打算','uk :prəˈpəʊz, us :prəˈpoʊz','[[ + that ] \n I propose that we wait until the budget has been announced before committing ourselves to any expenditure. \n 我建议我们在预算没有宣布以前不要有任何支出。 \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n He proposed dealing directly with the suppliers. \n 他提议直接和供应商打交道。 \n, She proposed a boycott of the meeting. \n 她建议抵制这次会议。 \n, He proposed a motion that the chairman resign. \n 他提出了一项让主席辞职的动议。 \n, To be nominated for union president you need one person to propose you and another to second you. \n 要被提名为工会主席，你需要有一个推荐人和一个附议人。 \n, I remember the night your father proposed to me. \n 我记得你父亲向我求婚的那个晚上。 \n, Now, if you\'d all please raise your glasses, I\'d like to propose a toast to the bride and groom. \n 现在，请大家举起酒杯，让我们为新郎和新娘干杯。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n How do you propose to complete the project in such a short time? \n 你打算怎样在这么短的时间内完成这个项目？ \n, [ + -ing verb ] \n How do you propose tackling this problem? \n 你打算怎么解决这个问题？ \n, I do not propose to reveal details at this stage. \n 我不打算在这个阶段透露细节。 \n, What we are proposing is a radical change in approach. \n 我们打算在方法上来个彻底转变。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo008.mp3'),('proposition','（通常指商业上的）提议，建议主张；观点；见解要求与（某人）发生性关系，向…提出猥亵的要求','uk :ˌprɒp.əˈzɪʃ.ən, us :ˌprɑː.pəˈzɪʃ.ən','[He wrote to me last week regarding a business proposition he thought might interest me. \n 他上周写信给我，提出一项他认为我会感兴趣的商业建议。 \n, I ve put my proposition to the company director for his consideration. \n 我已将我的提议交给公司主管考虑。 \n, They were debating the proposition that  All people are created equal . \n 他们正就“人人生而平等”这一命题展开辩论。 \n, I was propositioned by a complete stranger. \n 一个素不相识的人提出想和我上床。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukpropo011.mp3'),('protocol','礼仪，礼节（正式的国际性）条约，公约，议定书规程，协议（计算机之间交换信息的计算机语言）','uk :ˈprəʊ.tə.kɒl, us :ˈproʊ.t̬ə.kɑːl','[a breach of Royal protocol \n 对皇家礼仪的违反 \n, diplomatic protocol \n 外交礼仪 \n, The Geneva Protocol of 1925 prohibits the use of poisonous gases in war. \n 1925年通过的《日内瓦公约》禁止在战争中使用有毒气体。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprote013.mp3'),('prowess','杰出的才能；高超的技能','uk :ˈpraʊ.es, us :ˈpraʊ.es',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukp/ukpro/ukprowe001.mp3'),('psychedelic','迷幻的','Mí huàn de','\n','2019-12-10',1,0,0,'https://translate.google.cn/translate_tts?ie=UTF-8&q=psychedelic &tl=ja&tk=313923.196151&client=webapp&prev=input'),('puff','喘气气喘吁吁吸（烟），抽（烟）吹，喷出，冒出一小口（烟雾），一小股（空气）泡夫，松饼吹捧文字，吹捧的言论气喘吁吁，呼吸急促吸烟，抽烟','uk :pʌf, us :pʌf','[He came puffing up the stairs. \n 他气喘吁吁地上了楼。 \n, [ + speech ] \n  I ran all the way home,  she puffed (= said while puffing). \n “我是一路跑回家的，”她气喘吁吁地说。 \n, She was puffing on a cigarette at the 