wɒn.tɪ.tə.tɪv, us :ˈkwɑːn.t̬ə.teɪ.t̬ɪv','[quantitative analysis \n 定量分析 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukq/ukqua/ukquali017.mp3'),('quartz','石英','uk :ˈkwɔːts, us :ˈkwɔːrts','[]\n','2019-10-11',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukq/ukqua/ukquart004.mp3'),('ratify','（尤指政府或组织）正式批准，使正式生效，正式签署','uk :ˈræt.ɪ.faɪ, us :ˈræt̬.ə.faɪ','[Many countries have now ratified the UN convention on the rights of the child. \n 很多国家现在已经正式签署了联合国儿童权利公约。 \n, The decision will have to be ratified (= approved) by the executive board. \n 这个决议必须要经过管理委员会的批准。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukras/ukrasp_017.mp3'),('reactionary','反动分子；保守分子；反对进步者','uk :riˈæk.ʃən.ər.i, us :riˈæk.ʃən.er.i',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukray/ukrayon019.mp3'),('referendum','（就重大政治或社会问题进行的）全民公决，全民公投','uk :ˌref.əˈren.dəm, us :ˌref.əˈren.dəm','[Is it more democratic to hold a referendum, rather than let the government alone decide? \n 进行一次全民公决，而不是由政府自己作出决定，是不是要更民主些？ \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukred/ukredou021.mp3'),('regime','政府；政权；政体组织方法；管理体制；体系生活规则，养生之道（同 regimen）','uk :reɪˈʒiːm, us :reɪˈʒiːm','[The old corrupt, totalitarian regime was overthrown. \n 腐败的旧极权政府被推翻。 \n, The regime in this office is hard work and more hard work. \n 该事务所的管理方式是让人努力再努力。 \n]\n','2019-10-09',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregen008.mp3'),('regulation','规则，条例，法规；控制，管理一般的，普通的；规定的；正规的','uk :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.ʃən, us :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.ʃən','[safety/health/traffic/fire/security regulations \n 安全／卫生／交通／消防／保安条例 \n, The correct procedure is laid down in the rules and regulations. \n 正确的程序在规章条例中有规定。 \n, government regulation of inflation \n 政府对通货膨胀的控制 \n, businessmen in their regulation pinstripe suits \n 身着细条纹正式西服的商人 \n, It\'s regulation to wear suits at the office. \n 按规定在办公室要穿西服。 \n, a regulation football pitch \n 符合规范的足球场 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul006.mp3'),('regulatory','管理的；控制的；监管的','uk :ˌreɡ.jəˈleɪ.tər.i, us :ˈreɡ.jə.lə.tɔːr.i','[a regulatory body/organization \n 监管部门／组织 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul008.mp3'),('reinvent','（在已有事物的基础上）重新创造，改造（通过改换工作或形象、行为方式而）改造自己，洗心革面，换个活法','uk :ˌriː.ɪnˈvent, us :ˌriː.ɪnˈvent','[The story of Romeo and Juliet was reinvented as a Los Angeles gangster movie. \n 罗密欧和朱丽叶的故事被改编成了一部洛杉矶黑帮题材电影。 \n, He\'s one of those sportsmen who reinvent themselves as TV presenters. \n 他是那些半路出家做电视节目主持人的运动员之一。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01196.mp3'),('reiterate','反复地说，反复讲；重申','uk :riˈɪt.ər.eɪt, us :riˈɪt̬.ɚ.eɪt','[The government has reiterated its refusal to compromise with terrorists. \n 政府重申拒绝向恐怖分子妥协。 \n, [ + that ] \n She reiterated that she had never seen him before. \n 她一再重申自己以前从未见过他。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukreg/ukregul030.mp3'),('relativity','相对论相对性','uk :ˌrel.əˈtɪv.ə.ti, us :ˌrel.əˈtɪv.ə.t̬i',NULL,'2019-10-03',0,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrej/ukrejec021.mp3'),('relieve','缓解，减轻，解除（疼痛或担忧）；使宽心，使宽慰缓和，缓解（令人不快的局势）救济；救援；救助接替；换…的班；替下将（某地从敌人的围困中）解围；解救撒尿，排尿（urinate 的礼貌性说法）','uk :rɪˈliːv, us :rɪˈliːv','[She was given a shot of morphine to relieve the pain. \n 医生给她注射了一针吗啡来止痛。 \n, She relieved her boredom at home by learning how to type. \n 她在家学打字来打发无聊的时光。 \n, New toll roads could help relieve congestion on other routes. \n 新建的收费道路可以帮助缓解其他道路的拥堵情况。 \n, emergency food aid to help relieve the famine \n 为了救济饥民而提供的紧急食品援助 \n, I\'m on duty until 2 p.m. and then Peter is coming to relieve me. \n 我要值班到下午两点，两点以后彼得就会来换班。 \n, An armoured battalion was sent to relieve the besieged town. \n 那个城市被困，一个装甲营被派去解围。 \n, He proceeded to relieve himself against a tree. \n 他走到一棵树旁小解。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrel/ukrelen014.mp3'),('repulse','赶走，驱逐；击退（尤指进攻）；拒绝，拒绝接受令人厌恶；使人反感击退；败退；拒绝','uk :rɪˈpʌls, us :rɪˈpʌls',NULL,'2019-09-25',1,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrep/ukrepro011.mp3'),('reputation','名誉；声望；名望','uk :ˌrep.jəˈteɪ.ʃən, us :ˌrep.jəˈteɪ.ʃən','[The company has a worldwide reputation for quality. \n 这家公司的产品质量誉满全球。 \n, She has the reputation of being a good doctor. \n 作为一名优秀的医生，她很有声望。 \n, His reputation was destroyed when he was caught stealing some money. \n 他偷钱时被当场抓住，这使他声名扫地。 \n, The hotel has a bad/good reputation. \n 这家旅馆名声很好／坏。 \n, He earned/established/gained/acquired a reputation as an entertaining speaker. \n 他因为演讲妙趣横生而赢得／享有／得到／获得盛名。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrep/ukrepro016.mp3'),('rescue','救援；营救；解救救援；营救；解救','uk :ˈres.kjuː, us :ˈres.kjuː','[The lifeboat rescued the sailors from the sinking boat. \n 救生艇将水手们从正在下沉的船上救起。 \n, The government has refused to rescue the company from bankruptcy. \n 政府已经拒绝援助这家濒于破产的公司。 \n, Lifeboats carry out many rescues every month. \n 救生艇每月都会执行很多救援任务。 \n, We huddled together on the cliff ledge, waiting for rescue. \n 我们挤作一团蜷缩在悬崖边，等待救援。 \n, I didn\'t know anybody at the party, but the hostess came to my rescue (= helped me out of a difficult situation) by introducing me to a few people. \n 在聚会上我谁也不认识，但女主人过来救了我的驾，把我介绍给几个客人。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrer/ukrerun005.mp3'),('respirator','>人工呼吸器；呼吸机>防毒面具','uk :>ˈres.pɪ.reɪ.tə, us :>ˈres.pə.reɪ.t̬ɚ',NULL,'2019-10-03',2,1,0,NULL),('reveal','揭露；泄露；透露使显露；展现；显示（电视节目最后的）揭示','uk :rɪˈviːl, us :rɪˈviːl',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrev/ukrev__005.mp3'),('revere','>尊敬；崇敬','uk :>rɪˈvɪə, us :>rɪˈvɪr',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,2,0,NULL),('revert','回复','uk :rɪˈvɜːt, us :rɪˈvɝːt','[Please revert by email. \n 请通过电子邮件回复。 \n]\n','2019-10-03',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukc/ukcld/ukcld01216.mp3'),('revolution','（通常指改变政治体制的）革命革命性剧变；大变革旋转；绕转；循环运动（轮子等的）一转，一圈','uk :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən, us :ˌrev.əˈluː.ʃən','[The French Revolution changed France from a monarchy to a republic. \n 法国大革命使法国由君主政体变成共和政体。 \n, The country seems to be heading towards revolution. \n 这个国家似乎正在走向革命。 \n, a technological revolution \n 技术革命 \n, Penicillin produced a revolution in medicine. \n 青霉素的发现引起了医学上的一次革命。 \n, The revolution of the earth around the sun was proposed by Copernicus. \n 地球围绕太阳旋转这一观点是哥白尼提出的。 \n, Engine speed can be measured in revolutions per minute (abbreviation rpm). \n 发动机的速度可以每分钟转数（缩写为rpm）来表述。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrev/ukrevie017.mp3'),('ribbon','（捆扎或装饰用的）带子，丝带，缎带一缕；一条；一排勋带，绶带（打字机的）色带','uk :ˈrɪb.ən, us :ˈrɪb.ən','[Sandra often wears a ribbon in her hair. \n 桑德拉常在头发上扎条丝带。 \n, He tied up the present with ribbon. \n 他用缎带将礼物包扎起来。 \n, A ribbon of road stretched ahead of us across the desert. \n 沙漠中的一条路宛如一根细长的带子，在我们前方延伸。 \n, My typewriter needs a new ribbon. \n 我的打字机得换色带了。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrhy/ukrhyth008.mp3'),('ripple','涟漪；微波；细浪（声音的）传播起伏；（感情的）逐渐扩散彩条冰激凌（使）起涟漪；（使）如波浪般起伏','uk :ˈrɪp.əl, us :ˈrɪp.əl','[The stone she threw caused ripples to spread across the lake. \n 她扔了一块石头，湖面泛起阵阵涟漪。 \n, A ripple of laughter/applause, etc. ran through the crowd. \n 人群中响起一阵阵笑声／掌声等。 \n, A ripple of excitement/unease, etc. flowed up her spine. \n 一阵激动／不安等顺着脊背传遍了她全身。 \n, News of the war hardly caused a ripple (= people showed little interest). \n 战争爆发的消息几乎没有引起任何反响。 \n, raspberry ripple \n 山莓彩条冰激凌 \n, The breeze rippled the water. \n 微风在水面吹起阵阵涟漪。 \n, His muscles rippled under his skin. \n 他皮肤下的肌肉一条条凸起。 \n]\n','2019-12-11',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrip/ukripof003.mp3'),('rival','竞争对手；敌手可与…相媲美，比得上','uk :ˈraɪ.vəl, us :ˈraɪ.vəl','[He beat his closest/nearest rival by 20 marks. \n 他以领先20分的成绩打败了和他水平最接近的对手。 \n, The companies produce rival versions of the toy. \n 这些公司生产的玩具跟我们的产品争夺市场。 \n, No computer can rival a human brain for/in complexity. \n 没有任何计算机比得上人脑复杂。 \n, The beauty of the country is only rivalled by (= is as great in degree as) the violence of its politics. \n 该国的美丽风光非同寻常，而其国内政治的残暴同样惊世骇俗。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrip/ukripof021.mp3'),('rumble','发出隆隆声；发出辘辘声；发出低沉连续的响声发现，察觉，看穿（某人的秘密或非法事情的真相）打架；打群架','uk :ˈrʌm.bəl, us :ˈrʌm.bəl','[Please excuse my stomach rumbling - I haven t eaten all day. \n 不好意思，我肚子在咕咕叫——我一整天都没吃东西了。 \n, Thunder rumbled in the distance. \n 雷声在远处隆隆作响。 \n, Convoys of tanks rumbled (= moved while rumbling) through the city streets.\n, His boss eventually rumbled him, and he was sacked. \n 他的老板最终看穿了他，把他解雇了。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrum/ukrum__003.mp3'),('sack','大布袋；麻袋；大纸袋；大塑料袋食品购物袋开除，解雇（通常指在战争中）洗劫，劫掠（美式橄榄球）擒杀（四分卫）床床上功夫（好或差）解雇，开除（美式橄榄球）擒杀（四分卫）（通常指在战争中）洗劫，劫掠','uk :sæk, us :sæk','[The corn was stored in large sacks. \n 玉米装在大麻袋里。 \n, a sack of potatoes/coal/flour \n 一袋土豆／煤／面粉 \n, a sack of groceries \n 一袋食品杂货 \n, They gave him the sack for being late. \n 因为迟到，他们开除了他。 \n, Two workers got the sack for fighting in the warehouse. \n 两名工人因为在仓库打架而被解雇了。 \n, The sack of Rome by the Visigoths occurred in the fifth century. \n 西哥特人洗劫罗马发生在公元5世纪。 \n, The Colts have allowed only six sacks this season. \n 小马队本赛季只遭受到六次擒杀。 \n, It\'s late - I\'m going to hit the sack (= go to bed). \n 时间不早了，我要上床睡觉了。 \n, He came home and found Judy and Brad in the sack (= in bed) together. \n 回到家，他发现朱迪和布拉德睡在一张床上。 \n, They sacked her for being late. \n 因为迟到，他们把她开除了。 \n, He got sacked from his last job. \n 他上一份工作是被解雇的。 \n, The quarterback was sacked only once and completed 16 out of 23 passes. \n 这名四分卫只被擒杀过一次，23次投掷成功了16次。 \n, The invaders sacked every village they passed on their route. \n 侵略者洗劫了他们途经的每个村庄。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/ukr/ukrut/ukrutte018.mp3'),('salve','药膏；软膏；油膏慰藉，宽慰使良心得到宽慰；减轻内疚感','uk :sælv, us :sæv','[He salves his conscience by giving money to charity. \n 他通过向慈善机构捐款来使自己良心得到宽慰。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksal/uksalti013.mp3'),('sanctuary','庇护，保护；避难所，庇护所禁猎区，鸟兽保护区圣殿，圣堂','uk :ˈsæŋk.tʃʊə.ri, us :ˈsæŋk.tʃu.er.i','[Illegal immigrants found/sought/took sanctuary in a local church. \n 非法移民把当地的一座教堂当作避难所。 \n, The chapel became a sanctuary for the refugees. \n 这座小教堂成为难民的庇护所。 \n, igurative \n If I want some peace and quiet, I take sanctuary in my study. \n 如果想清静一会儿，我就躲进自己的书房。 \n, a wildlife/bird sanctuary \n 野生动物／鸟类保护区 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksam/uksampl014.mp3'),('sardonic','讥讽的，冷嘲的，轻蔑的','uk :sɑːˈdɒn.ɪk, us :sɑːrˈdɑː.nɪk','[a sardonic smile/look/comment \n 讥讽的微笑／嘲讽的表情／尖刻的评论 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksap/uksappy012.mp3'),('scandal','丑行；丑闻；震惊；反感丑闻报道丢脸，耻辱','uk :ˈskæn.dəl, us :ˈskæn.dəl','[a financial/political/sex scandal \n 财政／政治／性丑闻 \n, Their affair caused/created a scandal in the office. \n 他们的风流韵事在办公室里成了丑闻。 \n, The scandal broke (= became public knowledge) right at the beginning of the Conservative Party Conference. \n 就在保守党大会开幕的那一刻，丑闻曝了出来。 \n, If there is the slightest suggestion/hint of scandal, the public will no longer trust us. \n 只要有哪怕一丝丑闻，公众就再也不会信任我们。 \n, Some magazines contain nothing but scandal and gossip. \n 有些杂志专门报道丑闻，散播小道消息。 \n, to spread scandal \n 传播丑闻 \n, [ + (that) ] \n It s a scandal (that) children are treated in this way. \n 这样对待孩子真是太可耻了。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscamp004.mp3'),('scavenge','（从废弃物中）觅食；捡破烂（野生动物）以腐肉为食','uk :ˈskæv.ɪndʒ, us :ˈskæv.ɪndʒ','[The flood has left people and animals desperately scavenging for food. \n 因遭受水灾，村民和牲畜四处寻觅食物。 \n, We managed to scavenge a lot of furniture from the dump. \n 我们从当地的垃圾堆里捡到了许多家具。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl015.mp3'),('sceptical','怀疑的，持怀疑态度的','uk :ˈskep.tɪ.kəl, us :ˈskep.tɪ.kəl','[Many experts remain sceptical about/of his claims. \n 很多专家对他的主张仍然持怀疑态度。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksca/ukscarl026.mp3'),('scholar','（尤指大学的）学者聪颖好学者；善于学习者','uk :ˈskɒl.ər, us :ˈskɑː.lɚ',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksch/uksched030.mp3'),('screw','螺丝（钉）扭转，旋转监狱看守（尤为犯人用语）性行为；性伙伴（同 thumbscrew）用螺丝固定（或拧紧）（用类似螺丝的东西）固定，拧紧旋上，拧合（尤指出于不赞同或疼痛）扭曲（面部）将（尤指纸或布）揉成团拧牢，旋紧骗，欺骗（与…）发生性关系','uk :skruː, us :skruː',NULL,'2019-09-25',0,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukscr/ukscrap025.mp3'),('scrutiny','细看，仔细审查','uk :ˈskruː.tɪ.ni, us :ˈskruː.t̬ən.i',NULL,'2019-09-25',2,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukscr/ukscrum010.mp3'),('secede','退出，脱离（国家或政府）','uk :sɪˈsiːd, us :sɪˈsiːd','[There is likely to be civil war if the region tries to secede from the south. \n 如果这一地区想脱离南方而独立，很可能会爆发内战。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksea/uksear_030.mp3'),('secretarial','秘书的，文秘的','uk :ˌsek.rəˈteə.ri.əl, us :ˌsek.rəˈter.i.əl','[a secretarial school \n 文秘学院 \n, She s found some part-time secretarial work. \n 她找到了一份兼职的秘书工作。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/ukseces015.mp3'),('security','保护（措施）；安全（保障）保安人员保障；牢靠保证金；担保品证券；债券（在家庭或一段关系中）安全感；安心','uk :sɪˈkjʊə.rə.ti, us :səˈkjʊr.ə.t̬i','[The station was closed for two hours because of a security alert. \n 由于有安全警报，车站关闭了两小时。 \n, 30 demonstrators were killed in clashes with the security forces over the weekend. \n 周末，30名示威者在与保安部队的冲突中丧生。 \n, The tighter security measures/precautions include video cameras throughout the city centre. \n 加强安全保障措施包括在市中心安装摄像头。 \n, The students were deported because they posed a threat to national security. \n 这些学生因对国家安全构成威胁而被驱逐出境。 \n, The banks must tighten security against fraud. \n 银行必须加强安全措施，防止诈骗。 \n, The most dangerous criminals are held in maximum-security prisons (= prisons that are as difficult as possible to escape from). \n 最为危险的罪犯被关押在戒备最森严的监狱里。 \n, You\'ll need to notify security if you want to work late in the office. \n 如果想在办公室里工作到很晚，你需要通知保安人员。 \n, If it\'s a choice between higher pay and job security, I\'d prefer to keep my job. \n 如果在更高的薪酬和安稳的工作两者之间进行选择，我宁愿保住工作。 \n, I\'m on a temporary contract and have little financial security (= cannot be sure of having enough money to live on). \n 我签的是临时合同，没什么经济保障。 \n, She used her shares in the company as security against a $23 million bank loan. \n 她用自己在公司的股票作抵押向银行借了2300万美元。 \n, The hotel held onto our suitcases as security while we went to the bank to get money to pay the bill. \n 宾馆扣下我们的行李作为抵押，我们则去银行取钱来付账。 \n, Most children need the security of a stable family life. \n 大多数孩子需要稳定的家庭生活带来的安全感。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/uksecul006.mp3'),('seducer','引诱者；勾引者；诱奸者','uk :sɪˈdʒuː.sər, us :səˈduː.sɚ','[The play tells the story of a wealthy woman who seeks revenge on her heartless seducer. \n 该剧讲的是一个富有的女人试图报复一个引诱了她却又对她无情的人。 \n]\n','2019-11-08',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksec/uksecul020.mp3'),('seminary','神学院','uk :ˈsem.ɪ.nər.i, us :ˈsem.ɪ.ner.i','[]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksel/ukselfs024.mp3'),('severe','非常严重的；剧烈的；惨重的极度的；非常困难的不和善的；冷酷的；严厉的；苛刻的不加装饰的，朴素的，简朴的','uk :sɪˈvɪər, us :səˈvɪr','[a severe chest infection/leg injury/toothache \n 十分严重的胸腔感染／腿伤／牙痛 \n, This is a school for children with severe learning difficulties. \n 这是一所为有严重学习障碍的孩子设立的学校。 \n, In parts of Africa there is a severe food/water shortage. \n 非洲的一些地方存在严重的粮食／水资源短缺问题。 \n, There is expected to be a severe frost tonight. \n 今晚预计会出现严重的霜冻。 \n, Severe cutbacks in public spending have been announced. \n 已经宣布对公共开支进行大幅度削减。 \n, This will be a severe test of our strength. \n 这将是对我们实力的严峻考验。 \n, The headteacher spoke in a severe voice. \n 校长说话的口吻很严厉。 \n, The president is currently facing severe criticism. \n 总统目前正遭到严厉的批评。 \n, There are severe penalties for failing to declare all your income to the Inland Revenue. \n 未向税务机关申报个人全部收入会受到严厉的处罚。 \n, She wore a severe black dress, and plain black shoes. \n 她穿了一件朴素的黑连衣裙和一双普通的黑鞋子。 \n, I don\'t like these severe modern buildings. \n 我不喜欢这些没有任何装饰的现代建筑。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksev/ukseven007.mp3'),('sheepish','（因做错事或傻事而）窘迫的，不好意思的','uk :ˈʃiː.pɪʃ, us :ˈʃiː.pɪʃ','[She gave me a sheepish smile and apologized. \n 她窘迫地笑了一下，道了歉。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukshe/uksheat012.mp3'),('shelf','（通常指固定在墙上或橱柜中的）搁板，架子陆架，陆棚；岩棚（产品）现成的，不需订制的将…下架，不再出售','uk :ʃelf, us :ʃelf','[a glass shelf \n 玻璃架子 \n, on the top/bottom shelf \n 在顶层／底层架子上 \n, One wall had shelves from floor to ceiling, crammed with books. \n 一面墙是高及天花板的书架，上面塞满了书。 \n, It s often cheaper if you buy wallpaper off the shelf, rather than having to order it. \n 如果你买现成的墙纸，通常会比订购的要便宜。 \n, off-the-shelf goods/clothes \n 现成的货物／衣服 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukshe/uksheat023.mp3'),('siren','警报器，汽笛塞壬（古希腊神话中的海妖）妖妇，迷人而危险的女人','uk :ˈsaɪə.rən, us :ˈsaɪr.ən','[police sirens \n 警笛 \n, When the air raid siren went off people ran to their shelters. \n 空袭警报响起时，人们纷纷跑向掩蔽所。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksin/uksinle014.mp3'),('slang','俚语谩骂','uk :slæŋ, us :slæŋ','[army slang \n 军队俚语 \n, a slang expression \n 一句俚语 \n,  Chicken  is slang for someone who isn t very brave. \n chicken 是用来称呼胆小者的俚语。 \n, The players started slanging each other in the middle of the game. \n 比赛到中局阶段时，球员们开始互相谩骂。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksla/uksland004.mp3'),('slicked','熟练自如的，娴熟的油滑的，华而不实的浮油（同 oil slick）高级亮光纸印刷的杂志（同 glossy magazine）使（头发）光滑，使亮滑','uk :slɪk, us :slɪk','[Manilow gave the slick, polished performance that we ve come to expect. \n 正如我们所期望的那样，马尼洛的表演挥洒自如、技艺精湛。 \n, A slick pass from Eaves to Brinkworth set up the goal. \n 布林克沃斯接伊夫斯的妙传射门成功。 \n, It s that sort of slick sales talk that I mistrust. \n 那种油腔滑调的推销宣传正是我所不相信的。 \n, He slicked his hair back with gel. \n 他打了发胶将头发向后梳平整。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksle/uksleep019.mp3'),('slippery','湿滑的，容易打滑的狡猾的，滑头的','uk :ˈslɪp.ər.i, us :ˈslɪp.ɚ.i','[slippery soap \n 湿滑的肥皂 \n, a slippery floor \n 湿滑的地板 \n, The road was wet and slippery. \n 道路又湿又滑。 \n, He s as slippery as an eel - you can never get a straight answer out of him. \n 他非常滑头——你永远无法从他嘴里得到直率的回答。 \n, He s a slippery customer (= person), and I ve never felt comfortable with him. \n 他是个狡猾的家伙，和他在一起我总是感到不舒服。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksli/ukslimm016.mp3'),('slot','狭缝；（尤指）投币口，狭槽（为某活动安排的）时段被（能）放于狭槽中','uk :slɒt, us :slɑːt','[I put my money in the slot and pressed the button but nothing came out. \n 我把钱放入投币口，按了按钮，但没有东西出来。 \n, The holder has slots for 100 CDs. \n 这个CD架的槽口可以放100张CD。 \n, The programme will occupy that half-hour slot before the six o clock news. \n 那个节目将在六点新闻前的半小时这一时段播出。 \n, The legs of the chair are meant to slot into the holes at the back. \n 椅子腿应该要插到后面的孔里。 \n, Do these two pieces slot together? \n 这两个部件能插在一起吗? \n, Slot piece A into piece B, taking care to keep the two pieces at right angles. \n 把 A 件插入 B 件，注意使二者保持正确的角度。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslo/ukslobb018.mp3'),('smack','（尤指作为惩戒孩子的方式）掌掴，打撞；使劲摔（作为惩戒手段的）打巴掌，掴（用握成拳的手）打呯的一声，啪的一声响吻海洛因不偏不倚地，正好径直，猛地；砰然作声地','uk :smæk, us :smæk','[I never smack my children. \n 我从来不打孩子。 \n, I ll smack your bottom if you don t behave yourself. \n 如果你表现不好，我就打你屁股。 \n, I smacked my head on the corner of the shelf. \n 我的头撞在了架子角上。 \n, She smacked her books down on the table and stormed out of the room. \n 她啪地把书摔在桌子上，气冲冲地离开了房间。 \n, You re going to get a smack on the bottom if you don t stop throwing your toys. \n 如果你再乱扔玩具，就该打屁股了。 \n, I gave him a smack on the jaw. \n 我一拳头打在他下巴上。 \n, She slammed her briefcase down on the desk with a smack. \n 她啪的一声把她的皮箱放到桌子上。 \n, a big smack on the lips \n 在嘴唇上的响亮一吻 \n, How long has she been on smack? \n 她吸海洛因多长时间了？ \n, She lives smack in the middle of Shanghai. \n 她住在上海市的正中心。 \n, S \n The kids are smack dab in the middle of the fight between their parents. \n 父母吵架时，孩子们被夹在正中间。 \n, I wasn t looking where I was going and walked smack into a lamppost. \n 我没有看路，直愣愣地撞到了灯柱上。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukslu/ukslutt010.mp3'),('soapy','含有肥皂的；像肥皂的','uk :ˈsəʊ.pi, us :ˈsoʊ.pi','[I soaked it in some soapy water and the stains came out. \n 我把它浸泡在肥皂水中，污渍就被洗去了。 \n, I used to think avocados tasted soapy when I was a child. \n 我小时候曾认为鳄梨的味道像肥皂。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksno/uksnows025.mp3'),('sophisticated','精于世故的，老练的；见多识广的；很有品位的精密的，复杂的；高级的','uk :səˈfɪs.tɪ.keɪ.tɪd, us :səˈfɪs.tə.keɪ.t̬ɪd','[She was slim, svelte, and sophisticated. \n 她身材苗条，体态娇美，处事练达。 \n, I don t think I have any books that would suit your sophisticated tastes. \n 我认为我没有什么书能满足你那高雅的品位。 \n, He was older than me and from London and I thought him very sophisticated. \n 他比我大，而且来自伦敦，我觉得他为人很老练。 \n, I think a more sophisticated approach is needed to solve this problem. \n 我认为要解决这个问题需要更为高明的方法。 \n, These are among the most sophisticated weapons in the world. \n 这些属于世界上最尖端的武器。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksoo/uksoon_012.mp3'),('sophomore','（美国大学或高中的）二年级学生','uk :ˈsɒf.ə.mɔːr, us :ˈsɑː.fə.mɔːr','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksoo/uksoon_015.mp3'),('sought','搜寻','uk :sɔːt, us :sɑːt',NULL,'2019-09-25',3,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksor/uksorel011.mp3'),('souvenir','纪念品；纪念物','uk :ˌsuː.vənˈɪər, us :ˌsuː.vəˈnɪr',NULL,'2019-10-03',1,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksouth007.mp3'),('spacious','宽敞的，空间大的','uk :ˈspeɪ.ʃəs, us :ˈspeɪ.ʃəs','[a spacious house/living room \n 宽敞的房子／起居室 \n, spacious accommodation \n 宽敞的住宿条件 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksou/uksouth030.mp3'),('spawn','（鱼、青蛙等的）卵小动物；小孩（使）产生，（使）突然增长产卵','uk :spɔːn, us :spɑːn','[isapproving \n He looked at me as if I was a spawn of Satan because I was smoking a cigarette. \n 他看着我的样子，仿佛是看到了恶魔一般，就因为我抽烟。 \n, The new economic freedom has spawned hundreds of new small businesses. \n 新的经济自由催生了上百家新的小企业。 \n, Her death spawned countless films and books. \n 她的去世催生了无数电影和书籍。 \n, The frogs haven t spawned yet. \n 青蛙还未产卵。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspa/uksparr017.mp3'),('species','（动植物的）种，物种','uk :ˈspiː.ʃiːz, us :ˈspiː.ʃiːz','[Mountain gorillas are an endangered species. \n 山地大猩猩属于濒危物种。 \n, Over a hundred species of insect are found in this area. \n 这一地区有上百种昆虫。 \n, igurative humorous \n Women film directors in Hollywood are a rare species. \n 女性电影导演在好莱坞属于稀有物种。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspeci007.mp3'),('speculate','猜测；推测，推断投机，做投机买卖','uk :ˈspek.jə.leɪt, us :ˈspek.jə.leɪt','[I don t know why she did it - I m just speculating. \n 我不知道她为什么那么做——我只是猜测。 \n, A spokesperson declined to speculate on the cause of the train crash. \n 一位发言人拒绝就火车相撞事件的原因作出推测。 \n, Journalists are speculating about whether interest rates will be cut. \n 记者们在猜测是否会降息。 \n, [ + that ] \n The newspapers have speculated that they will get married next year. \n 报纸猜测他们明年会结婚。 \n, He made his money speculating on the London gold and silver markets. \n 他在伦敦黄金市场和白银市场上做投机生意赚了钱。 \n, The company has been speculating in property for years. \n 这家公司做房地产投机生意已经有好几年了。 \n]\n','2019-12-24',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspe/ukspect003.mp3'),('splintered','（木头、玻璃、塑料等的）尖细条，尖碎片裂成碎片','uk :ˈsplɪn.tər, us :ˈsplɪn.tɚ','[The girl had a splinter (of wood) in her toe. \n 女孩脚趾上扎进了一块（木头）碎片。 \n, The edges of the plastic cover had cracked and splintered. \n 塑料罩子的边缘裂成了碎片。 \n, igurative \n The danger is that the Conservative Party may splinter into several smaller political parties. \n 危险在于保守党可能会分裂成几个小的政党。 \n]\n','2019-12-19',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee010.mp3'),('spondulix','（幽默的说法）货币；钱，金钱；财产','uk :spɒnˈduː.lɪks, us :spɑːnˈduː.lɪks','[]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspl/uksplee028.mp3'),('spreadsheet','（尤用于商务的）电子表格程序','uk :ˈspred.ʃiːt, us :ˈspred.ʃiːt','[]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukspo/ukspotl019.mp3'),('square','正方形，四方形正方形物，四方形物（城镇中的）广场（常包括周围的建筑）（游戏中棋盘的）格直角尺，丁字尺古板的人；老古董使成平方；使成二次幂正方形的，四方形的（与长度单位连用）平方的（紧接长度单位后）…见方正的；相等的；水平的两清的，互不欠账的平局的直线的，笔直的乏味的；古板守旧的使成平方；使成二次幂（表示决心已定）挺起胸膛，挺直身子','uk :skweər, us :skwer',NULL,'2019-09-25',0,2,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquab010.mp3'),('squishy','软弱','uk :ˈskwɪʃ.i, us :ˈskwɪʃ.i','[ squishy banana\n, he whole idea of what constitutes a disability is squishy. \n, he definition of spam is squishy - a message that you delete I may think is a worthwhile offer.\n, hey feel he is too squishy on issues such as the rights of suspected terrorists.\n, he toy shop has a range of squishies for kids who love to squeeze, squish, and squash. \n, quishy white bread\n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english/uk_pron/u/uks/uksqu/uksquee019.mp3'),('staircase','（建筑物内通常带有扶手的）楼梯','uk :ˈsteə.keɪs, us :ˈster.keɪs','[She descended the sweeping (= long and wide) staircase into the crowd of photographers and journalists. \n 她走下又长又宽的楼梯，来到摄影师和记者中间。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksta/ukstabl030.mp3'),('statistical','统计的；统计学的','uk :stəˈtɪs.tɪ.kəl, us :stəˈtɪs.tɪ.kəl','[statistical errors/evidence \n 统计错误／证据 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksta/ukstate017.mp3'),('stomp','迈着重重的步子走；（尤指）怒气冲冲地走（常指为表示生气）跺（脚）；重踏，重踩','uk :stɒmp, us :stɑːmp','[She stomped up the stairs and slammed her bedroom door. \n 她噔噔噔地上了楼，重重地关上了卧室的门。 \n, He woke up in a bad mood and stomped off to the bathroom. \n 他一觉醒来心情不佳，噔噔地踩着重步走向浴室。 \n, The little boy was stomping his foot and refusing to take his medicine. \n 那个小男孩跺着脚不肯吃药。 \n, She stood by the road, stomping her feet to stay warm. \n 她站在路边，跺着脚让自己暖和些。 \n, I wish those people upstairs would stop stomping around. \n 我希望楼上那些人别再乱跺脚了。 \n, Why did you stomp on that insect? \n 你为什么要踩那只虫子？ \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksto/ukstoma003.mp3'),('strategy','战略；策略；计谋；行动计划；策划，部署','uk :ˈstræt.ə.dʒi, us :ˈstræt̬.ə.dʒi','[The president held an emergency meeting to discuss military strategy with the Pentagon yesterday. \n 总统昨天召开紧急会议，跟五角大楼商讨军事战略。 \n, Their marketing strategy for the product involves obtaining as much free publicity as possible. \n 他们对这一产品采取的市场策略包括尽可能去争取免费宣传的机会。 \n, [ + to infinitive ] \n We\'re working on new strategies to improve our share of the market. \n 我们正在制订新策略来增加我们的市场份额。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukstr/ukstrat003.mp3'),('summit','峰会，首脑会议，最高级会议山顶，顶峰顶峰，极点，巅峰','uk :ˈsʌm.ɪt, us :ˈsʌm.ɪt','[a summit meeting \n 首脑会议 \n, World leaders will meet next week for their annual economic summit. \n 世界各国领导人将在下周齐聚一堂，参加一年一度的经济峰会。 \n, On this day in 1784, Dr Michel Paccard and Jacques Balmat reached the summit of Mont Blanc. \n 1784年的今天，迈克尔‧帕卡德医生和雅克‧巴尔马特登上了勃朗峰的顶峰。 \n, I certainly haven\'t reached the summit of my career. \n 当然，我还没有达到事业的巅峰。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksul/uksulta014.mp3'),('supervised','监督，管理，指导','uk :ˈsuː.pə.vaɪz, us :ˈsuː.pɚ.vaɪz','[The UN is supervising the distribution of aid by local agencies in the disaster area. \n 联合国正在监督灾区的地方机构发放救援物资。 \n, The children play while two teachers supervise (= make certain that they behave correctly and are safe). \n 孩子们在两位教师的监管下玩耍。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksup/uksuper030.mp3'),('surly','脾气坏的；不友好的，粗鲁无礼的','uk :ˈsɜː.li, us :ˈsɝː.li','[We were served by a very surly waiter. \n 为我们服务的侍者态度很差。 \n, He gave me a surly look. \n 他很不友好地看了我一眼。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurge008.mp3'),('suspend','停止，暂停，中止（因犯错而）暂令停职；暂令停学；暂令停止参加活动悬挂悬浮，漂浮','uk :səˈspend, us :səˈspend','[The ferry service has been suspended for the day because of bad weather. \n 因为天气恶劣，渡船已经停开了。 \n, The country\'s president has suspended the constitution and assumed total power. \n 总统废除了宪法，独揽大权。 \n, When you go to the theatre, you have to be willing to suspend disbelief (= to act as if you believe that what you are seeing is real or true, although you know that it is not). \n 去戏院看戏时你得对剧情深信不疑。 \n, I\'m suspending judgment (= not forming an opinion) on the book I\'m reading until I\'ve finished it. \n 把书读完之前我不会作任何评价。 \n, Mr Young was given a six-month jail sentence, suspended for two years (= if he commits another crime within two years, he will have to go to prison for six months for his original crime). \n 杨先生被判监禁6个月，缓期2年执行。 \n, She was suspended from school for fighting. \n 她因为打架而被勒令停学。 \n, He was suspended for four games after arguing with the referee. \n 跟裁判发生争执之后，他被停赛4场。 \n, The builders worked on wooden platforms, suspended by ropes from the roof of the building. \n 建筑工人站在用绳子从房顶上吊下来的木制平台上作业。 \n, It was very uncomfortable lying on the hospital bed with my legs suspended in the air. \n 我躺在医院的病床上，腿悬吊在半空，难受极了。 \n, The drug is suspended in a saline solution. \n 这种药悬浮在生理盐水中。 \n, A cloud of smoke was suspended in the air. \n 空中飘浮着一团烟雾。 \n]\n','2019-10-08',1,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksur/uksurro024.mp3'),('sustain','保持，维持，使持续，使继续维持…的生命，供养经历，遭受（尤指破坏或损失）（情感上）支持','uk :səˈsteɪn, us :səˈsteɪn','[The economy looks set to sustain its growth into next year. \n 看来经济的增长会持续到明年。 \n, He seems to find it difficult to sustain relationships with women. \n 他似乎觉得和女人维持关系并不容易。 \n, S \n The judge sustained (= accepted) the lawyer s objection. \n 法官接受了律师的反对意见。 \n, The soil in this part of the world is not rich enough to sustain a large population. \n 这里的土地不够肥沃，无法供养大量的人口。 \n, She sustained multiple injuries in the accident. \n 她在这次事故中多处受伤。 \n, Most buildings sustained only minimal damage in the earthquake. \n 在这次地震中，大多数建筑物受到的破坏都很小。 \n, The company has sustained heavy losses this year. \n 公司今年遭受了严重的亏损。 \n, She was sustained by the strength of her religious faith. \n 宗教信仰的力量支撑着她。 \n, The love of my family and friends sustained me through my ordeal. \n 家人和朋友的爱支撑着我渡过了难关。 \n]\n','2019-12-13',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/uksus/uksuspi003.mp3'),('swath','长条区域，大块区域；（尤指）长条田地，大块田地部分；范围绷带，布条，带子（用布）裹，绑，包，缠','uk :sweɪð, us :sweɪð','[Huge swathes of rainforest are being cleared for farming and mining. \n 为了耕种和采矿，大片大片的雨林被砍伐。 \n, These people represent a broad/wide swathe of public opinion. \n 这些人代表了广大人民的意见。 \n, His head was wrapped in swathes of bandages. \n 他的头上缠着绷带。 \n, He came out of the hospital swathed in bandages. \n 他从医院出来时身上缠满了绷带。 \n, I love to swathe (= dress) myself in silk. \n 我喜欢穿丝绸做的衣服。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswa/ukswast004.mp3'),('swathe','长条区域，大块区域；（尤指）长条田地，大块田地部分；范围绷带，布条，带子（用布）裹，绑，包，缠','uk :sweɪð, us :sweɪð','[Huge swathes of rainforest are being cleared for farming and mining. \n 为了耕种和采矿，大片大片的雨林被砍伐。 \n, These people represent a broad/wide swathe of public opinion. \n 这些人代表了广大人民的意见。 \n, His head was wrapped in swathes of bandages. \n 他的头上缠着绷带。 \n, He came out of the hospital swathed in bandages. \n 他从医院出来时身上缠满了绷带。 \n, I love to swathe (= dress) myself in silk. \n 我喜欢穿丝绸做的衣服。 \n]\n','2019-10-07',0,1,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswa/ukswast004.mp3'),('swell','肿胀，肿，膨胀（音乐声等）变大，增大，变响亮（缓慢的）波涛起伏（乐器）音量的变大极好的极好地','uk :swel, us :swel','[It was obvious she had broken her toe, because it immediately started to swell (up). \n 她的脚趾显然已经骨折，因为立刻肿起来了。 \n, The group recruited more members, swelling its ranks (= increasing its size) to more than 1.3 million. \n 这个团体招募了更多会员，总人数已超过130万人。 \n, iterary \n His heart/breast swelled with pride (= he felt very proud) as he stood watching his son graduate. \n 当他站在那里观看儿子的毕业典礼时，心中充满自豪。 \n, That s a swell idea! \n 那个主意好极了！ \n, Everything s going swell. \n 一切都很顺利。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet002.mp3'),('swells','肿胀，肿，膨胀（音乐声等）变大，增大，变响亮（缓慢的）波涛起伏（乐器）音量的变大极好的极好地','uk :swel, us :swel','[It was obvious she had broken her toe, because it immediately started to swell (up). \n 她的脚趾显然已经骨折，因为立刻肿起来了。 \n, The group recruited more members, swelling its ranks (= increasing its size) to more than 1.3 million. \n 这个团体招募了更多会员，总人数已超过130万人。 \n, iterary \n His heart/breast swelled with pride (= he felt very proud) as he stood watching his son graduate. \n 当他站在那里观看儿子的毕业典礼时，心中充满自豪。 \n, That s a swell idea! \n 那个主意好极了！ \n, Everything s going swell. \n 一切都很顺利。 \n]\n','2019-12-20',0,0,0,'https://dictionary.cambridge.org/ja/media/english-chinese-simplified/uk_pron/u/uks/ukswe/uksweet002.mp3'),('sympathy','同情（心），理解慰问，吊唁，吊慰支持，赞同支持参加罢工以支持（某人）','uk :ˈsɪm.pə.θi, us :ˈsɪm.pə.θi','[The president has sent a message of sympathy to the relatives of the dead soldiers. \n 总统已经向阵亡士兵的家属发去了唁电。 \n, I don t have much sympathy for her - I think she s brought her troubles on herself. \n 我不太同情她——我觉得她是在自找麻烦。 \n, I went along to the funeral in order to offer my sympathies. \n 我去参加了葬礼以表吊慰。 \n, I must confess I have some sympathy with his views. \n 我必须承认我比较赞同他的观点。 \n, Of those people questioned, 93 percent s